Child stood up in ride as it started and fell out, striking face on concrete.
Ferris wheel stopped abruptly.  Two patrons fell from seat and landed on another child who was getting off the ride.
injury_desc: 1) Fracture of left eye orbit requiring surgical insertion of metal plate with screws, and about 70 stitches.  2) Bruises on head, side, and leg.  3) Double vision and disorientation.

acc_desc: Guide wheel failed, causing trolley structure to misalign and engage the track.  Car stopped abruptly, injuring 7 children and 2 adults.
injury_desc: Back and neck pain, headaches, muscle soreness.  1 patron suffered a seizure during the evacuation.

acc_desc: Sweep #6, while in air, suddenly came down, hitting ride, then ground.
injury_desc: Contusions to face, abrasions to back

acc_desc: Patron tripped on bumper rail.
injury_desc: Bruised knee, shoulder, elbow, loose front teeth.

acc_desc: Worn pawl caused safety restraint to release when child was upside down.
injury_desc: Hit head on ceiling of car and hit chest on restraint bar.  Transported by ambulance.  MRI showed compressed vertebra in neck.

acc_desc: 9-year-old took younger child on teacup ride.  Younger child was wearing an "arm leash" device used to restrain children in crowded places.  Leash became entangled in car hub area beneath wheel used to turn car.  While trying to untangle the leash, the 9-year-old suffered traumatic amputation of two fingertips.
Brake failure resulted in abrupt stop, throwing 3 riders against restraints/car interior.
injury_desc: 1) Abdominal injuries requiring surgical removal of part of intestines; 2) broken nose, facial cuts and bruises; 3) lacerations and abrasions to face

acc_desc: Patron's pant leg caught in dolley assembly located under car.
Child ejected from car when centrifugal force caused him to let go of the lap bar.  He came out through the opening at the lower side of the gondola.
injury_desc: Struck by another car, then fell down ride platform.  Suffered multiple abrasions and contusions, and a deep puncture wound and laceration on left leg.

acc_desc: Child ejected from car due to centrifugal force.  Child's parents said he fell from between the lap bar and the side of the car.
injury_desc: Bruises to upper leg.  Transported to hospital, treated and released.

acc_desc: Child was riding with two older boys when he fell out of the car.  A witness said that she noticed the car was spinning fast.  She further stated that the boy had looked ill and that he came out from over the top of the side of the car.
injury_desc: Transported to hospital, treated and released.

acc_desc: Rider was getting back into his go-kart when he was hit by another kart.
injury_desc: Laceration on right leg, possible fracture.

acc_desc: Overweight adult patron was ejected from seat, striking car structure and another patron, and falling from ride.
injury_desc: 1) Contusions and abrasions.  2) Broken collarbone and bruised knee.

acc_desc: Amusement ride hit fence, dislodging light fixture, which hit patron on head.
Electric wire energized fence child was holding.
Ride's hydraulic hose caught on spinning ride passenger carrier.  The broken hose caused two cars to open, but no one fell from the moving ride.
injury_desc: Nine patrons sustained minor injuries.  Local firefighters evacuated the ride.

acc_desc: Roller coaster car crashed into another car, due to ride operator error and defective chain dog.
injury_desc: 2 children complained of neck and back pain.

acc_desc: Coaster's speed caused child's head to come out side of car on a curve, where her face hit a fence.
Child received electrical shock from touching light socket.

Car started sparking.  Operator told patron to stay in car while he shut off ride.  While escorting patron from car, patron was shocked when her  pocketbook energized through contact with metal floor.
Intoxicated patron attempted to board ride car, slipped and fell between cars.
injury_desc: Cut forehead, bruises to chest, pelvis, arms, and legs.

acc_desc: Child's head hit left side of roller coaster.
injury_desc: Cut over left eye, lethargic, limp, pupils constricted, responded to painful stimuli only.  Transported to ER.

acc_desc: Child was playing on queue rails waiting to ride.  He fell, injuring his head.
Two children bumped heads.
Two children, ages 12 and 13, collided.
Patron misjudged step while stepping down into boat.  She stumbled and twisted knee in an outward motion.
Patron hit in head by an unidentified object.
Patron attempted to stop while on waterslide, in order to avoid a person walking in front of the slide.
Patron fell on steps while exiting.
Child slipped and fell, hitting head on concrete
Child ran a go-kart "hot" into the pit and collided with an unmanned go-kart.
Child's head became entrapped inside a suction drain box.  Near drowning.
injury_desc: Head injury, near drowing.  Admitted to hospital.

acc_desc: Child jumped off end of an inflatable obstacle course and landed on his arm.
Child fell while entering wave pool and hit head on concrete.
Child driving go-kart collided with kart in front of him.
12-year-old girl driving go-kart collided with kart driven by an 11-year-old boy.  The boy suffered rib/internal injuries.
Patron apparently lost control of his go-kart and ran "hot" into the pit area, colliding with the containment system.
Child sustained head injuries when she exited a kiddie coaster running toward the entrance, and collided with an incoming car.
Child fell from a stair climb of a children's participation area.
Two double-passenger go-karts collided, causing one to spin out and collide with the containment system.
Child tripped over edge of a support pillar and ran into post.
Child fell while trying to exit a kiddie plane ride by herself.
Woman tried to stop a swinging gym ride on which her child was riding.  The ride had been left unattended (no operator).
injury_desc: Broken leg and pelvis.  Admitted to hospital.

acc_desc: Patron fell off tube and hit head on concrete bottom.

Child sustained electrical shock when she touched the fence of a merry-go-round ride.  The shock was caused by a hot wire coming into contact with the control box which was making contact with the fence.
Child driving go-kart tried to avoid contact with another kart and collided with the containment system.
Two children, ages 6 and 8 were found not breathing in wave pool.  A witness reported that the children were playing a game, attempting to see who could hold their breath and stay underwater longest.
injury_desc: Near drowning.  Both children admitted to hospital.

acc_desc: Admission to hospital caused by suspected ingestion of chlorine fumes.  No other information in Amusement Ride Safety Division office.
injury_desc: Inhalation of chlorine fumes.  Admitted to hospital.

acc_desc: Toddler stood up and jumped from kiddie rocket ride.
injury_desc: Admitted to hospital.  Injury not specified in report.

acc_desc: Patron sustained neck in jury when the Gravitron ride operator was "horseplaying" and fell on her.
Patron stepped off or jumped from shallow end of wave pool.
One rider broke left front tooth in half and chipped right front tooth while riding a roller coaster.
injury_desc: Broke left front tooth in half and chipped right front tooth

acc_desc: Patron jumped the queue line to avoid paying entrance fee.  The trespasser later jumped an upper queue line into a ceiling area obscured by artificial fog.  The trespasser walked into a guardrail and somersaulted into a 10-foot-deep fog pit.
injury_desc: Patron transported to a local hospital with head, shoulder, back, and neck injuries.

acc_desc: Rider lapsed into unconsciousness on coaster, was transported to hospital, and died two days later.
Flyer landed on cushions and broke ankle.
Flyer broken arm during an improper landing.
Flyer suffered hairline fracture to leg while landing.

Patron broke both wrists when patron braced arms between the moveable lap bar and the fixed handrail on the front of the boat, with elbow braced on the lap bar and hands braced on the fixed rail.  The forward impact at the bottom of the drop allowed the patron's weight to move the lap bar forward enough to compress the patron's arms and break both wrists.
Patron fell onto the ground near the entrance to a spinning ride.
Monorail train collided with a palm tree blown onto the guide way by a summer thunderstorm.
injury_desc: Patron suffered chest pains.  Transported and admitted to hospital.

acc_desc: Flyer broke left ankle during improper landing.
Flyer broke left ankle during improper landing.
Patron lapsed into unconsciousness shortly after riding the roller coaster, was transported to a local hospital and died the next day.
Flyer was transported to local hospital with possible dislocated/broken ankle resulting from improper landing.
Worker suffered a fatal injury resulting from a 14-foot fall into an open elevator pit at a ceiling float ride.
Maintenance worker broke an arm and received leg injuries resulting from fall while performing structural repair on a roller coaster.
Patron fractured right ankle during an improper landing.
Patron broke leg after the driver of a two-seat go-kart crashed into a wall at a go-kart track.

Child managed to exit a spinning ride while the ride was spinning and was dragged under the ride for 3/4 of a revolution before the ride could be stopped.  The rigid lap bar engaged the larger rider seated next to the victim, but left sufficient room for smaller victim to silp out of the vehicle and be run over by the trailing vehicle.
Patron sustained injuries to toes by striking a windmill fan during flight.
Patron landed in the catch basin of a water raft ride at a waterpark.
injury_desc: Patron was admitted to local hospital complaining of upper back pain.

acc_desc: Patron jammed arm on the lap bar of a boat ride.
Two trains collided at low speed.  The impact tore the roof off the second coach.
injury_desc: Five passengers were admitted to a local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron jammed right wrist while going into the trough area of a water ride.
Low speed collision between two trains on a roller coaster injured 4 operations workers.
injury_desc: 4 people transported to local hospital with minor injuries.

acc_desc: Patron was injured after exiting a steep water slide and colliding with far wall at the splash pool.
injury_desc: Patron transported to a local hospital.

acc_desc: Toddler was standing up when the operator started the ride.  He fell out of the car and was run over by the next car.
injury_desc: Laceration of the back.  Treated at local hospital and released.

acc_desc: Child received 2-inch cut on her head while in a Fun House.  The child became confused and went into the wrong area.  She was caught between the "Rocking Room" and the fence when her head was cut.
Toddler fell while boarding Ferris wheel.  The boy apparently climbed over the back of the seat and fell about 6 feet to the bed of the trailer.
injury_desc: Child had no noticeable injury, but left with paramedic.

acc_desc: Child fell while trying to exit the ride.  As the ride was coming to a stop, the operator would open the gate on each passenger compartment as it went by him.  In order to assist riders off the ride, the operator attempted to jog the compartment around to the operator's station.  The operator moved the ride just as the child started to get out.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Treated at local hospital and released.

acc_desc: Incident reported.  No details available.

A man injured his foot on the Ferris wheel.  It is unknown how the injury occurred.  During the loading process, the operator, patron, or spectator released the brake on the 'old style' wheel and the weight of the wheel caused it to rotate.
A child was injured on a Jungle of Fun.  No details are available.

A woman was injured after the coupling pin between two Himalaya cars came out.  The first car after the disconnected hitch rotated around the sweep arm and ended up bottom side up under the second car.  It was fortunate that these cars were not occupied.  The fourth car, the one in which the woman was riding, did not get damaged during the incident.  The investigation revealed that in order for the connecting pin to come out, an 'R' key would have to have been lost or removed from the end of the pin.

A boy received a cut on his leg when exiting a Hustler ride.  Investigation revealed that this incident was caused by the loss of a bolt that holds the seat in place, and horseplay by the patron.  The seat cushion moved and exposed a piece of angle iron which cut the boy's leg.
A 31-year-old woman and her 3-year-old daughter were injured when a carousel telescope apparently jammed and an overhead beam fell on them.
injury_desc: The woman received a head laceration and the daughter received a bump on the head.

acc_desc: Child's foot was between the lap bar mechanism and the side of the car when the operator lowered the lap bar.
Child broke her arm while going down inflatable slide.  Near the bottom of the slide, her body began to twist and she fell on her right arm.
Patron was disoriented getting off ride, fell onto the platform, and injured his upper arm.
Child injured her arm while jumping down slide.
Child sustained possible broken leg when he jumped off a Sizzler ride before the ride had come to a complete stop.
A Moon Walk owner reported that his insurance company had received a claim for a broken arm.

A boy, age unknown, and a friend were on a kiddie ride.  The boy apparently got out of the car while the ride was rotating.  The operator, seeing the boy on the platform, hit the emergency stop.  Before the ride came to a complete stop, another car hit the boy and pushed him into the fence.
injury_desc: The boy was transported to the hospital, treated for scrapes and bruises, and released.

acc_desc: Police report states that a five-year-old boy sustained a possible broken leg while going down the toboggan slide.  No further information is available.
A nine-year-old girl got wood splinters in her right thigh when going down a toboggan slide.  No further information is available.

Patron was on a Spin Out ride when a power failure left her in an upside-down position.  The power was restored before the operator could engage the battery powered backup system.  The woman got off complaining of neck pain.

The operator had pushed the stop button and was waiting for the ride to stop.  As the ride slowed, several riders jumped from their seats.  Moments later the ride started turning faster.  Police investigation revealed that the guard around the center hub shifted and hit the control rod, which caused the ride to start turning.
injury_desc: Eight people injured.  Two of the eight were sent to the hospital and parents of the six signed medical release forms.

acc_desc: Passenger compartment came off the ride, injuring one adult and one child.  Investigation showed evidence that grease was getting into the area where the shaft seated on the sweep.  The hot weather may have contributed to the excess grease.  The mounting bolts were checked on Saturday and came loose on Sunday.  It is believed that the excess grease enabled the lock bolt to come out and the passenger compartment to fall off.
injury_desc: Child had bruised cheek.  Adult had pain in wrist.

acc_desc: A woman called to report tha ther son had been injured at a go-kart track.  Her son's kart was hit when another patron's kart did a 180 and drove into oncomgin traffic.  The karts' wheels hit each other and the woman's son was thrown out of his kart.

The scenery that runs along the seats fell forward, hitting an adult patron in the head.  Investigation revealed the R-keys, which secure the two pins that hold the scenery in place, came out, allowing the scenery to fall forward.
injury_desc: Head injury.  No information available on the extent of injury.

acc_desc: 17-year-old girl felt pain in her leg as she was going down chute.  The pain resulted from a sliver of wood, 2-3 inches long, which had punctured her snow pants and jeans, and embedded itself in her leg.

An incident occurred at a go-kart track that resulted in the death of a 3-year-old girl.  The Division did not find out about the incident until the following evening, when a reporter called for information.  The Palatine police confirmed the fatality.  As of May 2, 2001, the incident was still under investigation by the Division.
Child stuck his hand under the wheel on the Fire Engine car he was riding in.

Child fell out of the ride.  Investigation revealed that the nut had come off of one of four eye-bolts supporting the seat.  This allowed the seat to tip and the passenger to fall.
Child injured his foot when he got off the ride before it had stopped moving.
A girl, age unknown, was hurt while boarding the ride when her companion pulled the door down and hit her in the head.

injury_desc: Heart attack.  Paramedics transported to *** Medical Center.

acc_desc: Guest lost his tube and was standing on the flume when he was struck by another guest who knocked him down.  First guest struck his head.
injury_desc: Laceration to head.  Transported to medical facility.

acc_desc: Guest claims ride moved forward from the start, injuring her back.
Guest was found disoriented.  She said she was bumped from behind on ***.
injury_desc: Disorientation.  Paramedics transported to *** Medical Center.

acc_desc: Guest slipped while exiting slide and hit chin on side of flume.
injury_desc: Laceration on chin.  Parents transported to ER for possible stitches.

acc_desc: After riding, guest got dizzy and sick and started vomiting.
injury_desc: Dizziness and vomiting.  Treated at *** Medical Center.

acc_desc: Child attempted to exit the ride  before it came to a complete stop.  Once out of his car, he was hit in the head by another car.
Guest struck by another rider while coming down the slide.
Guest was riding in a double tube and bumped her rear end halfway down the slide.
Guest says the vehicle went side-to-side, injuring her wrist.
injury_desc: Wrist injury.  No broken bones.  Patron is taking a steroid medication.

acc_desc: While descending down the large drop, the guest's palm received a 1" laceration.
injury_desc: 1" laceration to palm.  Treated at *** Hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was riding with spouse and claims she hit her head on the inside of the tube.
injury_desc: Complained of head and neck pain.  Transported to ER.

acc_desc: Guest stepped into the train and stepped back out again to put her purse on the exit dock.  She turned and lost her balance and fell on the dock.  She did not believe that she came into contact with the train when she fell.
Guest was in *** with his son.  They bumped heads and she injured her nose.
Guest dove out of the 6-man raft when it reached the bottom of the slide.  He could not remember what happened after that.
injury_desc: Disoriented, asking repetitive questions.  Transported to hospital.

acc_desc: At the end of the ride, the guest was in and out of consciousness.
injury_desc: Loss of consciousness.  Paramedics transported to *** Medical Center.

acc_desc: While swimming, child hit heads with another guest.
injury_desc: Hematoma lateral to right eye.  At parents request, child was sent to ER via ambulance.

acc_desc: Guest filed complaint 17 days after visiting park, alleging head, neck, and back injuries from riding ***.
injury_desc: Head, neck, and back injuries.  Treated by chiropractor.

acc_desc: Guest complained of chest pain after riding.  He was admitted to hospital and later was found to have had a heart attack.
Guest rode slide and fell out of his tube, hitting his side on the slide.
Riding down a double tube and tube flipped over.  Patron hit his shoulder on the slide.
injury_desc: Patron's girlfriend drove him to ER.  Diagnosed with fractured clavicle.

acc_desc: Child was coming down on double tube.  She fell out and hit her shoulder on the wall of the slide.
Guest stated that when boat started coming down the drop, she ducked her head, hitting the seat back in front of her and then her head whipped back.
injury_desc: Complained of neck pain.  Transported to *** Med. Center.

acc_desc: Guest was riding on a double tube slide when his mouth hit the slide.
injury_desc: Chipped tooth.  Mother took child to dentist.

acc_desc: Guest slid down kids' slide head first.
injury_desc: Neck pain and abrasion to right hand.

acc_desc: Guest felt "snap" in his back while riding ***.  Ride owner claims guest has history of neck and back problems.
Guest bumped heads with another guest in wave pool.
injury_desc: Guest vomited several times and seemed lethargic.  Transported to hospital.

acc_desc: Guest started to fall sideways and tried to grab the handrail.  He heard a popping noise in his right wrist.

injury_desc: Examined by urologist on July 6, resulting in hospitalization for kidney stone treatment.

acc_desc: Guest got dizzy and complained of neck pain.  Does not remember hitting anything.
injury_desc: Neck pain, dizziness.  Transported to ER.

acc_desc: As the guest was exiting the ride, the restraint fromt he seat in front of him hit him in the head.
injury_desc: Lacerations to head.  Transported to ER for suturing.

acc_desc: Rode down slide in tube.  Toward the end of the ride the tube turned and she hit her head.  She stayed on the tube the entire ride.
injury_desc: Complained of head and neck pain.  Transported to ER.

acc_desc: Child attempted to cross the track in front of the coaster after the train had stopped.  She attempted to jump the track and fell through.

injury_desc: Laceration to nose.  Transported to ER.

acc_desc: Guest was sitting in an inner tube in the wavepool and bumped into another guest.

acc_desc: When car pulled into the dock at end of ride, child stuck his hand outside the train.  It became caught between the train and the lap bar release mechanism.

acc_desc: Guest suffered rapid breathing and numbness in fingers and around mouth.
injury_desc: Transported to ER, treated and released.

acc_desc: Unknown guest stretched his legs, hitting woman's toes with the heel of his shoe.

acc_desc: Guest was stepping into the entryway of slide, lost her footing, and fell.  Her head hit the slide.
injury_desc: 1" laceration on left eye/eyebrow.  Drove herself to *** for sutures.

acc_desc: Guest flipped out of double tube.

acc_desc: Child was riding the slide when she bumped her chin on the side of the slide.

acc_desc: Guest says that she slammed into the person in front of her when the ride stopped.

acc_desc: Child was riding with her mom.  She stated that as she was going through the loop, her head went forward and as she came out of the loop her head was thrown backwards.

acc_desc: A support rod brake came off on one car, causing it to collide with car in front.
injury_desc: Adult complained of tingling in hip and lower leg pain.  Child received bump on head.

acc_desc: While attraction was coming to a stop, guest lost her balance and fell off the horse.

acc_desc: Guest complained of chest pain at the end of ride, but refused medical assistance.  Guest then walked to main entrance and requested help.

Guest riding in front passenger side holding onto side railing so wouldn't slide into a friend.  When the car stopped, the guest's shoulder popped.
Guest saw a wave, dove into water, but it was too shallow.  She hit her chin on bottom.

acc_desc: Guest's mat skimmed across the water at the runout area and she landed hard on her chest.  She was sore when she got off the ride.  Pain continued to increase.  Later that night, she was taken to ER.

acc_desc: Guest hit her head on the back of her husband's head.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Felt dizzy and nauseous.  Transported to ER.

acc_desc: Guest fainted just before the train entered the station.  She only speaks Spanish.

Child was exiting the attraction when she tripped on edge of turntable.

acc_desc: After spinning on the ride, guest complained of dizziness.

acc_desc: Guest complained of dizziness and shortness of breath after riding.

This ride has 4 speed slides. The guard at the top dispatches all 4 slides and waits for them to clear before dispatching the next 4 riders. Just before this incident occurred, the lifeguard dispatched all 4 slides. The guest on slide #8 did not go down the slide with the other riders. The guard walked over to speak with the guest and told her to "go" several times. In the meantime, it seems that a 10 year old girl who does not speak english boarded slide #7. When she heard the lifeguard instructing the other rider to "go" she went down the slide, but the lifeguard did not see this. The guard waited for the girl on slide #8 to clear the catch pool before dispatching the next group. The girl in slide #7 took longer to go down the ride and was not clear when the next group dispatched. She was struck by a 14 year old boy a she was exiting the catch pool. She complained of back pain and was taken to the hospital for observation.
injury_desc: Complained of back pain.  Transported to ER.

acc_desc: Guest's mother says that her daughter bruised her ribs when the ride came to a sudden stop.
injury_desc: Bruised ribs.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest was in park on 8/18/01 when she complained of chest pain.  She claimed to have difficulty breathing and discomfort ever since riding roller coaster on 8/15/01.

acc_desc: Guest complained of nausea and dizziness after riding the attraction.

injury_desc: Transported to ER, treated and released.

The neurosurgeon who operated on the child told state officials that the injured had a pre-existing congenital cervical abnormality.

acc_desc: Child suffered injury to her hand while touching exit gate and railing.  She said she got "electrocuted" on both hands twice within the space of one minute.  A friend helped her away from the ride, and said that she felt something, too, when she touched the girl.  Following the episode, the child complained that she could not feel her arm.  Police at the scene noticed a red mark across her palm.  The child said the hospital told her she'd been shocked with 220 volts, but that she was okay.
injury_desc: Hospitalized overnight for observation due to concern about electrical shock.

acc_desc: 2-person kart spun out causing 2nd 2-person kart to collide with it head-on.
injury_desc: Two patrons taken to hospital.  One patron appeared somewhat "out of it" or delirious, as if she were drifting off.

acc_desc: Carnival employee was standing on the fencing to put "R keys" in the top outer scenery during setup of the ride.  The power had been turned on and he received an electrical shock (60 volts DC).
injury_desc: Employee told police and paramedics he felt alright and refused further treatment.  He also spoke with an ER doc via telephone and repeated to him that he felt alright.

acc_desc: Child drove into the pit area at full speed, colliding with a cement embankment
Tension cable failed on bungee jump, causing child to suddenly fall, bouncing off the edge of the air pillow and striking his head on the pavement.
injury_desc: Transported via ambulance to local ER, then flown by helicopter to Westchester County Hospital where he was admitted to the Intensive Care Unit with a head injury.

acc_desc: Child fell off ride while in motion, and was run over twice by the ride.  Scrambler was being operated as dark ride.  Child was allowed to ride alone on bench seat without seatbelts.  Witnesses say child may have been kneeling on seat when she fell off.
injury_desc: Died from head and multiple body injuries.

acc_desc: While trying to remove one train from operation, operator error resulted in the collision of two trains with guests on board.
injury_desc: Five guests were injured.  Three were transported to the hospital, treated and released.

acc_desc: Toddler riding in front seat of car climbed out during ride cycle, fell off, and was run over by next car.
injury_desc: Child's head was run over by one or more cars.  Transported to hospital, treated and released.

acc_desc: 5-year-old and 3-year-old fell out of roller coaster in mid-cycle.
injury_desc: 5-year-old suffered laceration to leg requiring 18 stitches; 3-year-old suffered scrapes and bruises to arm.

acc_desc: When train was released from the station it did not engage the chain at the bottom of the lift hill.  The train rocked back and forth and then suddenly engaged the train.
injury_desc: 5 patrons suffered whiplash-like conditions and were transported to local hospitals.

acc_desc: Car #6 catastrophically failed at 160 degrees from operator station.  Two patrons were ejected and another suffered minor injuries.
injury_desc: 1 patron died; 1 was hospitalized in serious condition; 1 was treated at the hospital and released later that day.

acc_desc: Train derailed in tunnel forcing train #1 underneath locomotive
14-year-old girl was riding on an amusement ride for approximately 90 seconds when she slumped over in her seat.  The child stopped breathing and subsequently died.
injury_desc: Death from cardiac arrhythmia due to Long Q/T Syndrome.

acc_desc: 22-year-old woman died while riding Sizzler carnival ride, approximately 60 seconds into the ride cycle.
injury_desc: Coronor could not determine cause of death, but said most likely cause was cardiac arrythmia.  Tissue sections revealed very few disease processes.  She was significantly overweight.  "It is further noted that this young woman was recently delivered of a full term infant.  One could reasonably imply that the decedent MAY have had relative iron deficient anemia secondary to that pregnancy.  There may also have been lingering fluid redistributions associated with her post partum state such that centrifugal forces produced during the ride may have altered blood flow to the brain.  All of these ride-related physiologic changes are but speculative at best and clearly not proven."

acc_desc: During a ride cascade stop, orange train that was stopped in zone 8 was struck from behind by the purple train.
injury_desc: 33 patrons injured, ranging in age from 6 to 51.  All were treated and released from local hospitals.

acc_desc: A 4-year-old girl entered the funhouse with her mother and older sister.  While on the top level, the victim lost her balance and fell to the floor with her hand partially landing on an 18" rotating disc.  The disc was rotating in a CW direction as was an adjacent rotating floor disc that other patrons were turning with their feet.  The victim's finger became wedged between the rotating floor plate and the stationary diamond plating.
Over-the-shoulder restraint system failed during ride cycle, fatally ejecting 50-year-old woman.
46 year old male suffered broken ankle while participating on inflatable ride.
injury_desc: Admitted to *** Hospital. Ankle required surgery.

acc_desc: 10 year old female collided with an attendant on water/tube slide.
injury_desc: Suffered head trauma.  Transported and admitted.

acc_desc: 18 year old female reportedly bumped her head while riding Villain Roller Coaster.
injury_desc: Reportedly traveled home, went to local hospital and kept overnight for observation.

acc_desc: 8 year old male slid down obstacle course ride slide head first instead of feet first.
injury_desc: Broke left elbow.  Admitted to *** hospital, elbow required surgery.

acc_desc: 2 year old male collided with another male participant on an inflatable bounce.
injury_desc: No treatment on site but went to Hospital later.  Multiple leg fractures, admitted, surgery to install rod.

acc_desc: 63 year old female became ill at park, had been on rides. Transported to hospital that night and had surgery to remove blood clot from brain.  Reported hitting head while riding Mantis roller coaster.
15 year old male suffered broken neck while jumping on inflatable bounce (Bounce House).
5 year old male reportedly fell from Miler Kiddie Coaster Ride.
injury_desc: Transported and admitted to Southpoint Hospital with reported leg and internal injuries.

acc_desc: 34 year old female  reportedly fell from tube and hit head while riding Alberta Falls water ride.
injury_desc: Disoriented, memory lapse, transported and admitted to Firelands hospital.

acc_desc: 16 year old male driving go kart hit wall.
injury_desc: Leg injury.  Transported and admitted to hospital.

acc_desc: 11 year old male was rear ended.
injury_desc: Transported as a precaution, treated and released from the hospital.

acc_desc: 6 year old male hit his head when he flipped at the upper end of  the *** water slide.
injury_desc: He was transported treated and released.

acc_desc: 6 year old male hit his head when he flipped at the upper end of  the *** water slide.
injury_desc: He was transported treated and released.

acc_desc: After sliding down, child fell over onto her arm.  Due to severe pain in her arm, parents transported child to a nearby hospital.  Diagnosis was a broken arm.

Small child came off the slide at an awkward angle with some speed and hit the ground.  When she tried to brace herself before hitting the ground, the motion resulted in a broken arm.  She was taken by ambulance to the hospital.

Ride was in stop position; adult male patron leaned forward with one hand on lap bar to wave at his wife and the lap bar opened.  He fell out onto the steel platform below.  His daughter who was riding in the same car with him was unloaded and not injured. He was transported to area hospital with broken right leg, separated shoulder and laceration to right side of head.
injury_desc: Broken leg, separated shoulder and laceration to head

acc_desc: Female patron sustained a laceration at the top of her hand across her knuckles.  She was taken to the hospital and received 14 stitches.  Ride was inspected for sharp edges, none were found

Adult male patron says he sustained a small laceration on his hand from somewhere on the ride.  He created a scene and demanded to see the owner as he was aware of the same incident happening the previous day. He did not require medical attention.  Ride was inspected the previous day for sharp edges, none were found
Two teenage girls bruised their knees on the lap bar due to it not having the required padding.  Girls left event, further information on their condition unknown.

While ride was operating a small part flew off the ride.  Ride was immediately shut down and passengers were unloaded.  The ride was re-inspected and approved for operation.  No injuries were sustained.
Four-year-old girl pinched her finger in the gate door handle while exiting ride.  She was taken to a nearby emergency room with a laceration and possible broken finger.  Treated and released.
Patron slid down obstacle course and landed wrong.  Due to severe pain in her ankle and thumb, parents transported child to a nearby Urgent Care Center.  Diagnosis was a sprained ankle and thumb.
Patron rolled over onto her arm at the bottom of the slide.  Due to severe pain in her elbow, she was transported to a nearby emergency room for treatment.  Diagnosis was a broken elbow.
Patron slid down obstacle course slide and arm was caught behind her.  Due to severe pain in her wrist, a family member transported child to the Urgent Care Center.  Diagnosis was a broken wrist.

Parent was racing son through obstacle course. As she was climbing up the climbing wall, she slipped, fell down and twisted her ankle. After leaving facility, her ankle swelled so she went to a doctor.  Diagnosis was a sprained ankle.

Patron was stopped and got hit from behind by another driver.  Patron complained of neck and lower back pain.  Patron was taken to nearby hospital for possible neck and back injury.  Further information on condition unknown.

Patron unlocked and opened door to exit the ride while attendant was unloading passengers on the other side.  Patron's tub was located near the center support sweep and she slipped stepping out of the ride and tripped over the center support sweep.  Treated at scene by EMT and left with possible broken foot.  Further information on condition unknown.
Was riding ride she fell sideways striking her forehead on the armrest. Treated at scene by EMT and then taken to acute care clinic for possible stitches.  Further information on condition unknown.
While riding ride she leaned over to look out the side and hit her head.  Staff bandaged her eye at scene and she left with guardian.  Further information on condition unknown.

Patron said she hurt her back when she lost hold, slipped on the seat and slid under the seat belt.  Patron was taken to nearby hospital for possible back injury.  Further information on condition unknown.

Patron 1 stopped in the middle of the track for no reason and patron 2 ran into her kart.  This caused patron 2 to run into the kart in front of her.  Injured patron 2 was taken by ambulance to hospital.  Further information on condition unknown.

Patron stopped kart on track for no reason and got hit from behind by another driver.  Patron was taken from scene by parents complaining of neck and head pain to seek medical attention.  Further information on condition unknown.
Patron was stopped and got hit from behind by another driver.  Patron left scene complaining of neck and lower back pain.  Further information on condition unknown.

Driver was entering the pit area and was hit from behind.  This caused the driver to ram into the corner of the pit entrance and injury her wrist.  Parents took child to hospital with possible broken wrist.  Further information on condition unknown.

Patron was going down the giant slide and turned around to look at his grandson and started sliding sideways down the slide and twisted his ankle.  He was treated at the scene and then transported to hospital by ambulance for treatment.  Further information on condition unknown.
A small child complained of leg pain after riding the giant slide.  Parents transported her to the hospital for treatment.  Further information on condition unknown.

Patron lost her grip, slipped out of the seat and hit her right thigh.  Patron was taken to nearby hospital by parents for possible injury even though there were no visible signs of injury or bruising.  Further information on condition unknown.

While going down the giant slide on a burlap bag, patron was waving her arms in the air and lost her balance. When she got to the bottom of the slide she heard her right ankle pop.  Patron stated she was going to the hospital and left scene.  Further information on condition unknown.
While exiting the ride, he leaned over to place his foot on the deck, slipped and fell forward on his forearm.  Patron was treated at scene and then transported to hospital for treatment.

A man came to the owner stating he had ridden the slide 3 days earlier and injured his tailbone.  He stated he did not have insurance and needed to seek medical attention.  Further information on condition unknown.
The ride broke a hydraulic line while patrons were riding it and sprayed hydraulic fluid in the faces of several riders.
injury_desc: Three of the four patrons went to the hospital to have their eyes checked.  Further information on condition unknown.

acc_desc: While riding with her mother, the toddler attempted to climb out of the car and before the ride could be stopped she injured her leg.  She was treated at the scene and then transported to hospital by ambulance for treatment.  Further information on condition unknown.

While child was sliding down the slide in a seated position on a towel, she pivoted sideways and rolled over on her arm.  She was taken to the hospital by her parents.  Parents confirmed she had broken her right forearm.

Child fatally ejected from Sizzler. Safety investigators from the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission determined that the child placed her foot on the rim of the foot tub in order to brace herself against the ride's acceleration. She was wearing smooth-soled dress shoes, which slipped off the rim and created an instability resulting in the fatal ejection.  The ride manufacturer issued a bulletin following the accident instructing owner/operators to modify the lap bar.

On July 17, the mother of an unknown aged male child called this office complaining that a set of loose car keys in the floor board of the bumper car she and her son had been in had fallen through a hole in the floor.  She initially wanted to know if there shouldn't have been warning signs about not dropping or carrying keys in the ride.   After further questioning she advised the keys were hers and had been around her wrist on a coil spring type wrist key chain and her car key had been destroyed by the electrical arch when the wheel rolled over it (power is derived from a wheel instead of stinger pole on these bumper cars.)  And she'd had to incur expenses for a locksmith and a new car key.
injury_desc: When asked if her son was injured she advised her son had been burned on the leg by the sparks and when asked if he was transported to the hospital she said she'd taken him to the hospital.  Follow up investigation and inspection determined the woman initially wanted an immediate $200 from the operator to have a locksmith come and open her car and make her another key.  She later reduced the amount to $100.  The operator denied payment and later assured our Inspector that there had been no injury claimed at any time the woman or her son were at the facility and no mention was made of her taking the boy to a hospital.

Employee injured using slide improperly, sitting up instead of lying down.
Child bumped his mouth, chipping tooth.
First toboggan stopped halfway; patron sat there; another toboggan came down and hit first one.  Flume #2, section B-24
injury_desc: Three patrons injured, ages 4, 6, and unspecified.  Bruises, sore leg, swollen lip.  One transported in ambulance.

acc_desc: Ride stopped.  Roll shaft failed; fatigue due to bearing alignment.
Child flipped himself and chipped tooth.
Patron allegedly hit her head within the waterslide.
Rail spread and front truck of car dropped between rail (derailed).
injury_desc: Only person on car hurt, bruised.

acc_desc: Woman slipped and fell.  Children riding with patron stated that she was out of the boat and slipped on the platform while exiting.
Patron was coming down the exit steps when she slipped, twisted ankle, fell, and cut her leg.
Patron was riding Orbiter and her neck began to hurt.
A piece of filler on slide came off resulting in a cut to patron's heel.  Waterslide closed for night to repair.
Rear-ended in pit area.  The karts were shut off, but momentum kept the colliding kart going.
Guest slipped and fell on steps at waterslide. Capet was wet and slippery.
Patron's sibling was in chair behind her.  Before the ride started, sibling rocked swing causing it to hit patron.
Child ran into wall.
Child ran into wall.
Patron hit wall, bumped head on steering wheel.
Possible flip of body in slide; banged head, knee and elbow.
Go kart coming into pit area didn't slow down and slammed into a stopped kart.  Patron in stopped kart had already started to exit, in violation of operator's instructions.
injury_desc: Headache - back of head hit seat.  Scraped leg on back.

acc_desc: Customer fell causing a cut on bridge of nose and lip.  Plastic protective wires listed as cause of accident.
Employee was talking to patron, not paying attention, and got bumped.  Fell against roll bar of kart and hit chin.
Go kart slowed down and was hit from behind.  The karts were slowed down because of an accident that occurred elsewhere on the track (those riders were fine).
Operator inadvertently hit start button.
Operator inadvertently hit start button.
Pebble was shot from a gokart in front of her and hit her under left eye.
injury_desc: Cut and bruise under left eye.

acc_desc: Failed to lower feet into the water at the bottom as instructed.
Child was running up the slide steps and fell.
Rider lost balance while exiting bumper boat.
Patron on merry go round, stepped back off of ride before it came to a complete stop.  Someone thought she was trying to take a picture of child on ride.
Another person t-boned the child into a side of the track.
injury_desc: Neck was sore and red; headache

acc_desc: Child ran into funhouse mirror.

Motorcycle came off with rider on it.  Did not have the retainer pin installed.  Woman saw accident happen and put her arms out to catch the child.  This prevented him from hitting the fence and causing more severe injury.
injury_desc: Child riding cycle was injured as was the woman who "caught" him.  Extent of injuries not specified.

acc_desc: 14 year old boy was pinned underneath the ride.  Witness statements say the boy lost something from his pocket while riding the ride.  When the ride stopped, the boy went underneath to retrieve what was lost.

Himalaya came apart.  State inspectors could not determine what happened.  Two cars derailed from the ride and ended up underneath the center of the ride.  They could not find any missing pins or anything that looked suspicious on the ride.
injury_desc: Five patrons were transported to local hospitals.

acc_desc: Reports show that a boy hit his head on the way down the slide.  Mother said that boy had preexisting injuries before riding the slide, but that the boy had been released from doctors care to ride the rides.

A horse fell off, injuring a child and his aunt.  The woman was standing on the merry go round next to the horse while holding the child.  Reports states that the merry go round was traveling at a speed that was not safe.  It is believed that woman slipped and pushed the horse off its hanger.
injury_desc: The boy was treated and released.  The woman was admitted to the hospital.

acc_desc: Boy was hit by ride as it started.  No parental guidelines.  Boy was going down exit ramp.  Operator shut down ride but it was still moving and hit child.
Employee injured his elbow while performing maintenance on the ride when his safety harness slipped.  Rescuers used a truck with a boom to get worker down.
Back part of train derailed with 2-year-old child riding in first car.
Mentally challenged man was on ride with a worker.  He squirmed from seat of ride and fell a short distance.
Ride door opened while in operation; operator failed to secure pin.  Child hit head and lost consciousness.
Father and daughter riding together.  They did not hold onto the lap bar and the daughter fell.
Child climbing steps to the ride, slipped and hit his face.
Injuries to back and leg.  No further information provided.
Fell out of ride.  Log that created the ripple came loose.  Also, one of the weights on the car was loose.
Prelaunch mechanism let loose prematurely.  Catch mechanism flopped over in the landing, sending chair.
Woman and her son were knocked out of ride.  Pole came loose before ride started as they were getting seated.
Patron knocked out of ride.  She was fastened by seatbelt and was spinning the ride.  She let go of the wheel to hand on and slid out to the ground.
Loose board left behind during maintenance hit two children.
Two children fell off while going up slide when the wind slid the ride sideways.
injury_desc: Two children were transported to the hospital.  One was treated and released, the other was admitted overnight for observation.

acc_desc: Child was strapped in, but jumped out as the ride started and fell off.  The next car behind ran her over.
injury_desc: Cut above right eye.  Swelling and no movement of right leg above knee & hip.  Child was transported to the hospital.

acc_desc: Seven-year-old child boarded water dark ride by himself while his mother waited outside.  Investigators surmised that he left his boat, fell into the waterway, and was crushed between two submerged conveyors.  Operators told investigators that a boat came back around a short while after the boy boarded with only a wet shoe in it.  The operator removed the shoe and continued operating the ride.  The child's mother noticed that the same cars had made several loops and her child still hadn't emerged.  The ride was shut down and a search began for the boy.  He was found dead approximately 30 minutes later.
injury_desc: Child was crushed between two underwater conveyors and died of a head injury.

acc_desc: Employee was crushed to death while setting up ride.

Sweep arms lowered at a faster than normal rate near the end of the ride.  Passenger car guide wheels hit steel guide ring around the base of the ride harder than normal.  Three children suffered minor injuries when they struck the insides of their cars.
injury_desc: Bruises and scrapes.  One child went to the hospital, but left with her grandmother before she was seen.

acc_desc: Child lost grip while spinning a rotating tub mounted on a stationary center pole.  Her arm got trapped in the spokes of the wheel, causing a fractured elbow.
4-yo child fell out of moving kiddie ride and was run over by the next car.
injury_desc: Cuts to lip and ear, contusion to head.

acc_desc: Woman was fatally ejected from the ride mid-cycle.

Ride operator was hit by coaster cars.  The ride was empty of passengers at the time and the park was getting ready for closing.  A witness saw the operator jump onto the track as the cars were coming toward him.  It looked as if he was trying to stop the line of cars coming into the station, facing the lead car with his hands out in front of him.  The cars struck the operator, pinning him under the first car.
injury_desc: Fatal injuries included crushed pelvis, punctured aorta, lacerated liver.

acc_desc: Child fell or jumped from ride at about the halfway mark of the track, hitting ride fencing and pavement.  He was sitting alone in the first car.  Witnesses say the child unbuckled his belt and stood up prior to falling.
injury_desc: Transported to the hospital, treated for broken tooth, cuts and scrapes to head, chest, and legs.

acc_desc: Young child (two and a half) slipped out of seat while ride was in motion.  When the ride started, the child was sitting back in the seat.  As the chairs rose in the air, the child leaned forward, then back again, then slipped sideways.  His left leg was still sticking through the left side of the restraint, but the rest of him was sliding through the right side.  The parents yelled to the operator to stop the ride.  The child was able to hold on for a while.  When the ride slowed and the chairs got closer to the ground, the father tried to grab the child.  The father was thrown clear by the ride and impacted a fence.  When the child finally let go, his left leg was hung up in the chains and so was hanging upside down. He hit his head on the ground.
Kart track attendant was refueling kart that had run out of gas.  Gas tank blew up and ignited kart and bumper system tires, resulting in burns to passenger and attendant.
injury_desc: Passenger suffered first and second-degree burns to neck, shoulders, and back.  Attendant suffered first-degree burns to his face and loss of hair.

acc_desc: Child fell out of moving ride and was run over by oncoming cars.

Operator turned his attention away from ride during load/unload so he could put away a hose used to wash vomit from one of the tubs.  One of the sweeps began to rise while a woman and her daughter were getting in.  The operator came back, stopped the ride, and the riders got out.
3-yo child sitting in engineer's car with lap strap secured reached his hand out toward the wheel of the car.  The child's hand was crushed between the wheel and the track.
injury_desc: Severe laceration and crush injury.  Child was airlifted to a hospital for treatment by a reconstructive plastic surgeon.  Long-term outcome uncertain.

acc_desc: 3-yo child sitting in engineer's car with lap strap secured reached his hand out toward the wheel of the car.  The child's hand was crushed between the wheel and the track.
injury_desc: Severe laceration and crush injury.  Child was airlifted to a hospital for treatment by a reconstructive plastic surgeon.  Long-term outcome uncertain.

acc_desc: A 5-year-old girl was riding with two other children, ages 6 and 7, when she attempted to switch seats with another passenger and was thrown from the ride.
injury_desc: Child was transported to the hospital via ambulance, treated for a 2-inch contusion on her head, and released.

acc_desc: 6-year-old child riding alone in Giant Wheel panicked when the ride stopped while his car was near the top, climbed over the seat, and fell 70-80 feet to his death.

A 2-year-old boy exited the ride while it was moving.  By the time the ride came to a stop, the injured had been run over by two of the ride's vehicles, dragged 3-6 feet on asphalt, and was pinned underneath a 3rd vehicle.  Both operators were located on the opposite side of the attraction from where the child disembarked.  They were standing by the controls and were unaware that the child had fallen off.
injury_desc: Child was transported via ambulance to *** hospital and treated for road burn on his face, arm, and leg.

acc_desc: One of the Kite Flyer's support legs was set up over an old sewer line and the asphalt gave way, tipping the ride 45 degrees.  Several children were injured and a few were taken to the hospital.
injury_desc: Several children were reported injured and transported to the hospital.  No contact information available to follow-up.

acc_desc: Teenage boy dislocated his knee while riding.  Operator claimed the boy was riding improperly.
injury_desc: Dislocated knee.  Paramedics transported to ER.

acc_desc: 6-yo child's car came off sweep during ride cycle and flew up into the air.  Child was ejected and run over by other cars.
injury_desc: Deep cut, abrasions, and bruising on arms, scratches on cheek, two bumps on head.  Child sustained headaches for two weeks, has no memory of the accident.

acc_desc: As the ride was spinning, child scooted up the couch and moved sideways.  He hit his head on the ceiling and when he fell, struck the entrance rail.
*** coaster car went up the chain hill.  Chain went over to the side and the dawg came off the chain, causing the ride to jam about two feet up the hill.
injury_desc: Patron hurt her back and was transported to the hospital via ambulance.

acc_desc: Catastrophic structural failure caused ride to stop abruptly with the train partially out of the station.
injury_desc: Multiple patrons injured.  7 were taken to the hospital and treated for lacerations requiring sutures, contusions, and head injuries.

acc_desc: Child's shoe became entrapped between the rear wheel of the motorcycle she was riding on and the sharp-edged support bracket, resulting in a severe laceration to the foot.
injury_desc: Severe laceration (5.5 cm long, 2.5 cm wide, 2cm deep) requiring extensive medical treatment and 2 weeks in a wheelchair.  Long-term outcome unknown.

acc_desc: Woman was riding with two children.  While unloading, the tub lost contact with the loading platform and the woman fell to the deck.
injury_desc: Victim complained of pain her left side (ribs) and was transported to the hospital via ambulance.

acc_desc: Woman was riding in the car with her son.  At the end of the ride, their car collided with the car in front of her at the brake area prior to the loading zone.
injury_desc: Treated and x-rayed in the ER, diagnosed with foot sprain from torn ligaments.

acc_desc: Two people were injured while riding.  The first hit her head 3 times on a metal bar behind her head.  The second patron complained of excessive side-to-side motion resulting in neck pain.
injury_desc: One treated in first aid, the other transported to the hospital

acc_desc: Patron hit her head several times on a metal bar behind her head.
injury_desc: Treated at first aid station for headache and tight neck.  Later diagnosed with whiplash-like injuries.

acc_desc: Patron said that the ride came to a quick stop with her body lunging forward.
Foot area of tub disconnected from seat area while ride was in motion and lowered onto framework of ride.  Patrons feet were hit by the foot area of the tub as it contacted the ride frame.
injury_desc: Bruising, scratches, and swelling to calf and top of foot.

acc_desc: Operator inadvertently started the ride while 3 children were being loaded into a car, before the attendant had secured the boys' safety bar.  The load attendant clung to the front of the car and was lifted up as the car rose.  His weight imbalanced the car, causing it to tip up and eject the three boys from a height of 10 feet.  The loading attendant then let go of the car and fell to the ground without injury.
injury_desc: 8-yo boy broke both wrists.  Report does not state whether he was admitted.  The other two children were treated for minor injuries and released.

acc_desc: The train started with a jerk, causing a toddler seated in the rear of the train to hit his chin on the seat in front of him.
Child was riding upside down on the inclined couch, slid up and over the backboard panel and bounced around.
injury_desc: Bumps on her head, neck, and back; arm pain.

acc_desc: When the ride came to a stop, the patron was slumped over inside the ride, unresponsive with irregular breathing.  Her breathing and heart stopped after she was removed from the ride by paramedics.  She was revivied and transported to the hospital, but died three days later.
Patron injured her lower back while riding.
One of two tandem riders fell to her death when she pulled the release cord that was intended to start her swinging.
Ride attendant was fatally ejected while riding the attraction in an improper and unsafe position.

13-yo girl was riding with two other children, leaning head back and laughing, when her head struck another part of the ride.  She lost consciousness with her head back, and her head then struck the handle of the cup next to her.
Caught leg in door of Big Wheel gondola, causing her to fall as she exited the ride.
Sustained neck injury while riding.  Patron stated that her husband was holding the handle she should have been holding onto and the boart was sent down before she could find her own handle.
Sustained laceration above left eye while riding.
Safety bar hit patron in face as he was getting off.
Patron injured her head while riding.
Woman claimed to have suffered internal bruising from the lap bars.
Chipped front teeth on lap bar.

Female guest claimed to have sustained head injury after riding major coasters in the park.  She claimed this injury caused persistent headaches and a hospital visit disclosed a vertebral artery dissected.
Patron was jerked forward when ride stopped, knocking out her tooth.
Jerked around on coaster.
Lap bar came down and hit her nose.
injury_desc: May require surgery for damaged cartilage.

acc_desc: Injured back on water slide.
injury_desc: Compressed fracture of the lumbar vertebrae.

acc_desc: Another patron jumped in front of the line and collided with her on the ride.
An employee tried to help push her to start the tube, resulting in an injury.
Patron jumped over railing on the walkway at ***.  Slipped and slide down the hill and sustained laceration from a metal piece in the ground.
Claims that something flew in his eye while riding ***.
Patron came down speed slide and collided with another patron who came down before her, but had not exited the ride.
Stood up and hit her head on a crossbar.
Patron injured her ribs.
Jerked around on coaster.
Patron leaned back on strap and it broke.
Patron broke her ankle on rafting ride.
Female was riding *** and broke a few ribs.
Cut hands on the plexiglass.
Tried to get off ride prematurely and fell.
Patron jolted her back when the ride stopped.
Patron claimed serious neck injury and herniated disc when ride stopped.
injury_desc: Serious neck injury and herniated disc.

acc_desc: A sudden gust of wind hit, pushing patron into a tree branch.
Patron lost her footing while exiting coaster.
Harness was too loose, causing injury to patron's chest.

Slipped out of restraints; fatal fall.
Hurt neck.
Hurt left elbow

Slipped on steps

Guest fell while exiting boat.

acc_desc: Two patron's cars collided.
Guest was pinched between mother and ride car side.

Guest quickly moved head and neck during ride.
Guest's head hit other guest's head when ride car struck front car.
Guest lost balance and fell while exiting ride car.
Guest was rear-ended by another guest's car.

When guest was exiting ride car, hit right knee on cross bar.
During usual ride, bumped collarbone.
During usual ride, husband slid and pushed guest against seat side.
While exiting ride car, guest twisted knee.

Pulled shoulder.  Guest could not specify which ride.
Patron fell while exiting.
While getting out of ride, car tipped.
injury_desc: Scratched arm, face, and leg.  Transported by ambulance.

acc_desc: While the ride was stopping, child stood up and fell out of ride car.
injury_desc: Quarter-sized abrasion to left side of forehead.

acc_desc: Rear car bumped front car.
injury_desc: Shoulder, ear, and neck pain; bloody nose, lower lip cut, chipped tooth.  Patron transported via ambulance.

acc_desc: While exiting, swinging ride car bumped rider.
Car 6 skewed, causing Car 7 to go over Car 6's fender.
injury_desc: Bruising to right arm and face.

acc_desc: Train tipped over in turn 1.  Adult male stuck leg out of train as it tipped over and the train fell on it.  Child struck head as the train tipped over.
injury_desc: Possible fracture of leg; head injury

acc_desc: Child bumped head on slide.
Adult female's ankle and leg rolled underneath her as she reached the inflated pillow at the bottom of the slide.
Two bumper cars collided.  Passenger's mouth hit hard part of steering wheel.
Oval track struck trailer frame during normal operation causing ride to come to an abrupt stop with six riders on board.  No damage to passenger compartments.
Riders jumped from the car while ride was in motion after being scared.
Restraint opened mid-cycle.  Two child riders (ages 6 and 7) were ejected.  One child was hit in the head by the spinning ride.
injury_desc: Both were transported to the hospital, treated and released.

acc_desc: Patron with her son driving in a double seat go kart were mis-aligned coming into the pit. Go-kart hit the guard rail and then a cement corner.
injury_desc: Patron could not move her head left to right

acc_desc: Guest reached out to grab handrail in unloading area while the operator continued to move the boat to the next brake section.
Car was bumped from behind in the unloading area.
Came in contact with hydraulic fluid during ride.
Train derailed during course, causing pain to rider's arm.
Guest complained of back injury after his raft was bumped by another raft during the course of the ride.
Force of the water caused vaginal bleeding.
injury_desc: Vaginal bleeding occured shortly after riding the Speed Slide.

acc_desc: Rider received a chin laceration when she bumped the steering wheel after the vehicle in which she was riding was bumped by another vehicle.
Patron running off ride and tripped, cutting her foot on the main support bar.
Patron felt that she was slipping and put her foot up on the car in front of her to brace herself. She heard a snap and started experiencing pain in her leg.
injury_desc: Pain in lower part of the right leg, no deformation

acc_desc: Patron jammed toe on the back of the seat ahead.
injury_desc: Left great toe with toenail avulsion

acc_desc: Patron was coming down the slide and hit her foot off the side of the slide

acc_desc: Hurt right ear from two shots of air from ride.
Patron struck head at bottom of slide.
Bounced head into and hit the wall.
injury_desc: Bruise under right eye, minor swelling on bridge of nose

acc_desc: Patron was climbing and slipped. Ring on left hand got caught and patron received cuts on the ring finger.
injury_desc: Laceration/contusion to left ring finger. Some swelling.

A young rider broke a foot when a kiddie coaster was moved by the operator while riders were unloading from the ride.

A maintenance worker on a transportation ride received an electrical shock while working to recover a stopped train. The worker received severe burns and was admitted to the hospital for an extended period.

A rider on a roller coaster suffered severe head injuries when a smooth rock thrown from a 36th floor balcony struck the rider in the head as the coaster ascended the lift hill. The rider was admitted to the hospital for an extended period.

One rider suffered lower back pain after riding a roller coaster. The rider initially refused treatment, was transported to their hotel room onsite in a wheelchair, and requested an ambulance 90 minutes later. The rider remained in the hospital for approximately four days, however, the hospital would not release any injury details. The spouse of the rider reported a pre-existing back injury for the rider.

A ride operator stood in an incorrect position while a theatrical entrance door was lowered at a motion base ride. The operator pushed against the door bottom and this additional stress broke both ankles on the operator, who was released from the hospital 1/14/04

Patron was riding in tube with daughter. The tube flipped over on the last turn. Daughter was thrown clear from the tube and this patron remained in the tube. Daughter was treated in First Aid, but this patron was not. Telephone call on 6/11/07 stating this patron went for medical treatment.
Patron said he was in the pool of the East Coast Waterworks when a small bucket of water knocked him off balance and he struck his head. Mother will take patron to the doctor when they get home.
Mother stated patron was on the slide. She grabbed onto the netting and fell backwards striking her head on the slide.
Patron reported she was riding with her father, the tube flipped, and patron struck her head.
Flipped out of the raft
injury_desc: Contusions to upper and lower back

acc_desc: Patron was riding the second to the last car on the ***when she bumped her elbow. Patron had gotten nine stitches removed on 6/5/07 and this caused the laceration to open up and bleed.
Patron hit her mouth on a bar on the bumper car. She had slight bleeding around a lower tooth and the tooth next to that one was slightly loose. Patron wears a retainer for orthotic treatment.
Patron was on a blue raft with a friend. The raft flipped after entering the bowl, and the patron landed on her shoulder.
Patron stated she fell off the raft, hit her head, her friend fell on top of her, and she hit her head again.
Patron complained of lacerations to the left middle and ring fingers.
injury_desc: Lacerations to left middle and ring fingers

acc_desc: Patron stated the boat she was in stopped before the hill and the boat behind them ran into their boat.
Patron was riding with a friend. Towards the end of the ride, the boat took a sharp turn and flipped. Patron hit his head on the slide.

Patron reported while walking across rope bridge another patron crossed the bridge in the opposite direction causing the bridge to buckle catching her toes in the bridge. Patron was barefoot. Telephone call received stating patron was going for medical treatment.
Patron was walking in the East Coast Waterworks area and bumped his head on a squirt gun.
Patron's father stated that patron was playing in East Coast Waterworks and hit her head on a pole.
Patron was on the slide and struck the back of her head.
Patron stated that an unknown patron pushed him into a water gun.
Patron stated while riding the *** something hit his eye. Telephone call on 7/13/07 stating that patron went to his doctor.
Patron fell while getting off the raft at Whirlwind and hit her knee on the cement bottom of the pool.
Patron reported he hit his left side when the train came to a sudden stop.
Patron stated she hit her ear on the seat restraint of the ride and cannot hear as well in the left ear.
injury_desc: Left eustachian tube dysfunction and nasal allergies

acc_desc: Patron said that on a turn he jerked his head and broke his three front teeth off in the side railing of the car. Patron will be going to his dentist.
Patron stated she was on the ride, got bumped, and the steering wheel turned, twisting her wrist.
Patron stated she hit her head on something on the ride.
Patron stated his hand was crushed in the restraining bar on the ride.
Father stated patron was running into East Coast Waterworks and ran right into a bar.
Patron was on the bottom of the slide when another child came down the slide and struck patron in the mouth with his foot.
injury_desc: Chin laceration, missing left upper baby tooth and a right tooth is loose

acc_desc: Patron reported he originally went into wrong row and was trying to move to the next row when another patron put his restraint down on patron's hand. Patron reported the ride attendant released the restraint bar.
Patron stated she felt her neck snap back while riding the ***and felt severe pain in the neck and back.
Patron was getting on the ride. She sat down on the swing and looked to the rear to see if her friend was on the ride. her right ear ring hooked into the swing chain an lacerated her earlobe.
Patron attempted to get out of the swing while the ride was operating. Ride operator activated the emergency stop. Patron fell onto the pavement.
Husband and wife were riding the Chute Out and fell out of the tube. Wife had pain to her left ribs, and right knee and elbow.
injury_desc: Pain in left ribs, right knee and elbow

acc_desc: Patron stated upon entering he bowl of the ***, he struck his back
Patron stated she was running and ran into a pole, chipping four upper teeth.
Patron slipped off raft, was thrown back, and hit blue wall with back and head. Patron then went down ride and was unable to get up.
Patron twisted her ankle while exiting the ride and fell approximately four feet.
injury_desc: Right elbow, ankle, and forehead pain

acc_desc: Patron stated that her foot got caught on the foot stirrup which resulted in patron falling on her wrist.
Patron hit her head on the red pole while walking in East Coast Waterworks
Patron stated the raft flipped on the last turn of the ride.
Patron stated she felt a crack in her back when she went around the loop
The raft flipped as they approached the last turn of the tube. Patron was riding with his girlfriend.
Patron slipped going down the slide and hit the back of her head.

Patron was riding the *** with an adult. The raft got stuck. When the attempted to free it, they flipped, and patron struck her elbow. Call received on 8/10/07 stating patron was treating with a doctor.
Patron ran into a metal pole, hitting his head and falling to the ground.
Raft flipped on the last turn towards the exit of the tube. The patron bumped her head. Patron was riding in front of raft. Email received stating patron went for medical treatment.
Patron caught her fingers on the metal bar of the ride. She fell in the opposite direction which put pressure on her fingers.
Patron was playing, turned his head, and ran into a pole.
Patron was in the front of the tube coming down the slide when the tube turned sideways and patron hit her hand and head on the side of the tube. The tube did not flip.
Patron flipped out of raft and struck his head on the slide. Upon entering the receiving pool, patron struck his head again on the side of the pool.
Patron reported was getting off raft and her right ring fingers was pinched between the raft and the edge of the pool.

A 48 tear old male guest slipped on the landing above our Gang slide and hit his head. The guard at the pool below, heard him fall, looked up, saw him on the ground and then watched him roll over and sit himself up on the side of the walkway. The guard at the pool directly in front of him stopped the ride and asked him if he was alright. As he was being questioned, the guard at the pool below signaled for first aid and management.
injury_desc: The guest stated that he was 'unconscious for about 10 seconds' and 'wouldn't be able to stand.' We gave him and ice pack for his head and maintained C-Spine until EMS arrived. We decided to board him because he felt he couldn't get to his feet safely. He stated he had no neck or back pain, numbness, tingling, or loss of movement, he was just didn't want to get up. He went to *** Hospital for further evaluation.

The lifegaurd noticed a distressed swimmer, blew a long whistle blast and entered the water to assist the guest. During the rescue the guest became unresponsive. The lifeguard put the guest on the rescue tube and brought her to the side of the pool. Two lifeguards and the EMT extrecated the guest from the pool. The EMT opened the guest's airway, felt no breathing and administered an initial rescue breath. The guest coughed up water, began breathing on her own and regained consciousness. Guest was coherent knew her location and provided her personal information. EMS arrived.

Guest stated that she was riding the north flume (#2) with her son aon her lap. Guset stated upon exiting the flume she bumped her left ankle on the left foam stantion in shipwreck shoals. Guest was treated with ice and released to care of *** EMS.

Guest's family member stated that she felt dizzy and passed out while exiting the ride. Upon my arrival, I found Guest to be unconcious with wet towels on her head and a family member trying to wake her up. Guest's skin was hot, flushed, red, and clammy. She told me of no medical problems and her last oral intake was several hours ago. I administered high flow O2 at 15ml, Took vital statistics while a *** Police Officer held her head for C-spine. Family member spoke spanish and had difficult time communicating. I was told by a translater park employee that she did have tachycardia. Guest started to become responsive and was placed on a backboard and transferred to EMS stretcher. *** EMS dispatched paramedics and they transported Guest out of park for further treatment.

Guest slipped while exiting fishing village slide. Guest fell and bit through bottom lip. Guest walked to guest Information and informed Them. Witness Statement- At around 4:30pm on July 4,2005 I was standing at in-park Guest Information when a 7 year old girl and her mother came running up to the desk. The mothers hand ws holding a napkin to her daughters chin and mouth. Blood was running down her hand. First Aid was stanking at in park with me and called in a 600 V to dispatch. She then applied her gloves and proceeded to apply gauze to the wound. There has a cut under her lower lip and another on in the same place on the inside of her lip. She claimed she had fallen on fishing Valley and bit her lip. First Aid then applied an ice pack and transported her to the First aid base. She was then transported to the hospital via ambulance.

Lift two stop running, all other belts stopped. Maintenance found that actually the thermal on lift out one tripped, causing all other belts to stop within 10-20 seconds as the PLC logic reads. Motor protection worked the way its designed why it tripped we could not find out, it was reset and has not tripped since. Operations had a few guest getting nervous in boats, so the decision was make to evacuate guest only 8-10 Minutes into maitenance trying to restart the ride.
Patron tried to exit the boat as it was leaving the turn table and fell in the water.

Thermal overload on lift hill motor tripped, causing train fully loaded with guest to stop on lift hill. Thermal overload on motor protection tripped. We were very busy and running 2 trains as fast as the system would allow. I think the thermal did what it was suppose too do, however, it would not allow us to reset it fast enough, so we decided to evacuate the train on the lift hill after about 15-20 minutes. We evacuated 23 guest from train stopped on the lift hill. No incidents were reported, the other train was in the loading station at the time. We replaced the overload and a fuse we found that went bad.

A boat was slipping on lift 3 belt prior to station-due to a loose wheel getting caught up underneath it that had come off of boat # 8 left rear. Cotter key broke, allowing guide wheel to fall off of boat # 8, which somehow floated up and under one side of another boat causing it to get lifted up enough for the belt to slip underneath it on lift 3. Corter key broke, allowing nut to come of and pin fell out and wheel came off boat #8. The entire ride was evacuated 50-60 guest. Wheel was put back on with new corter key, all other boats were checked, found no other problems. New cotter key and nut werte installed on wheel, boat #8

As per Anthony Brown, he was driving a Go-Kart. He was involved in an incident where he struck a car, and a car struck him from behind. This incident happened around the west curve area. He was checkd out by *** security. Anthony said that friend would take him to the hospital. As per ride operator Planner Pencher, the incident occurred on the west curve between the curved and straight arrow painted on the track. Anthony was in the ride car (32) and hit an unknown car in front of him . He was then hit from behind by the motorcraft car (21). It was near the end of the race. Anthony was removed from the ride.Then ride was shut down following the incident. The two cars, Tide (32) and Motorcraft (21) were removed from the trade pending an investigation by an inspector. A state official called and cleared all the other cars to reopen. All the cars were reinspected by the maintenance department. At approximately 9:30pm on Sunday July 24, 2005 a woman came into our Guest Services office with a complaint about the High Seas. This woman was alone, with an empty baby stroller in her hands. This woman stated that her daughter was on the High Seas ride. While the ride was in motion her daughter some how was able to slide under the lap restraint. This woman, who I will now call the mother, stated that she yelled to the ride operator to stop the ride, but the ride operator did not hear her. The mother then went on to state her concerns about the safety of the ride and for her daughter. I listened carefully to the mothers concerns, and offered her a 6 ticket refund for the ride for both her and her daughter, which she graciously accepted. T then told her that I personally was going to go to the High Seas and speak to the ride operator about the incident, in which I did. After speaking with the ride operator, I found out the following. The mother and daughter were in boat #3. The mother was facing the sling shot ride, while the daughter was facing the ride operator. At the time of the incident, all 4 boats were in operation. While the ride was in motion the ride operator was watching all 4 boats. While watching the boats, an man tapped her on her shoulder as she heard the mother yelling 'stop'. The ride operator then hit the stop button for all 4 boats. While the ride was stopping, the mother proceeded to remove the daughater from her seat and place her in her arms. When the ride came to a complete stop, the ride operator went over to boat number 3. At this point, both mother and daughter were on the same side of boat(facing sling shot). The ride operator then asked if everything was ok, and the mothers response was 'I think this ride is not for us, I think we will choose something else.'
injury_desc: Ride operator at this point assisted both passenger off of the ride and gave the mother a six ticket refund for their ride. At approximately 10:30-11:00pm, the ride operator was on sweeping duty around the park, and saw the mother put her daughter on the NASCAR ride. The ride operator stated that both were smiling and happy, and that there was no sign that either were upset about the earlier incident on the High Seas.
