acc_desc: Guest was riding and felt neck pain during the last turn of the ride. She described the pain as a muscle strain. Guest sent to the hospital as a precaution.

Guest and his party walked in to first aid unescorted. Through a translator in the party, guest's mother stated that the child ran to board the ride and struck his head. What the guest struck his head on is unclear. Guest has small laceration on his head, advised mother to take him to a physician.

Guest was riding in a double tube with her husband and came out of the tube in the splash pool. She was struck in the neck by her husband. The park was informed on August 21, 02 that she had received treatment beyond first aid for a strained ligament in her neck.

Guest reported a small laceration above her left eye to the first aid department on the date of her visit. She returned to the park with no treatment beyond first aid. On December 6/2006 the guest requested from the park reimbursement for medical treatment for the laceration.

Guest was riding inside a tube on the *** ride on July 13, 2002. he came out of the tube during the ride and struck the side of the flume, injuring his mouth. Guest and parents left the park. On August 2, 2002, a claim was for reimbursement of dental expenses to treat a missing tooth.

Guest stated that while riding ***, she came off her tube and injured her toe and bumped her head. She left the first aid office without treatment. The park received a letter of representation from her attorney demanding settlement for medical treatment she subsequently obtained.
Guest experienced a heat stroke while participating in the ***

Guest and family were at the queue area for the *** waiting to board the attraction when the guest complained of increasing, severe abdominal pain to a park employee. The *** Medical Services team and *** Fire Department were dispatched along with a Chinese language interpreter as there was an extreme language barrier with the guest and family. During the assessment, it was learned that they had ridden *** about 30 minutes earlier. Although they did not make any direct correlation to the ride's motion or mechanical effects, they did indicate that the pain did not exist before riding and started after the ride experience. The guest was sent to the local hospital for further evaluation.

Guest walked in to the *** First Aid Station with complaints of low-back pain and a headache. A *** nurse assessed the guest, who stated that he was recently involved in a motorcycle accident that left him with back and head injuries as well as visible bodily wounds on his arms. It appears that he did not have any treatment post-accident. The nurse's assessment indicated elevated blood pressure. The guest then became ill. Paramedics were dispatched and based upon their assessment the guest was transported to the hospital. The guest did not associate his injury/illness to the ride upon arrival at first aid. No information was provided as to dome or vehicle. His wife associated his injury/illness to the ride during a discussion with *** supervisor related to payment of the hospital fees. Guest was released at approximately 7:30 PM.
injury_desc: lower back pain and headache, illness

acc_desc: Guest stated that prior to entering the ride vehicle she felt her knee "pop-out". Guest stated that she has a history of this which normally corrects itself by sitting. She thought it would correct itself before the ride was over but it did not.
Guest complained of chest pains that increased after riding attraction.
Guest stated he was struck in groin area by lap bar during load in. Guest completed ride and was treated at first aid for pain to testicles and released.

Guest rode vehicle #205. After the ride, guest complained of chest pains, dizziness, and began vomiting. *** was dispatched to the attraction and determined that the guest was experiencing an irregular heartbeat. During the exam, guest indicated that she had been experiencing chest pains and shortness of breath.

acc_desc: Guest rode attraction in vehicle #201, row 2, seat 1 on the left side. Guest advised the ride supervisor of the incident and provided him the piece of foam. He refused medical attention at the time. Later in the day, guest visited the lower lot first aid station where he was assessed for eye pain. Guest was sent to the local hospital and was released at approximately 8:00 PM.

Guest states that she rode *** some time between 1:15 - 1:30 PM. Guest states upon review of the warning sign, she contemplated not riding due to a history of dizziness and motion sickness. She then decided to ride anyway. One our after disembarking the ride, guest requested medical assistance.

Guest alleges via email received by Park's Guest Relations on 7/31/06 that while riding the attraction for the 3rd time in a row that her daughter's arm became lodged between the lap bar and the seat.

acc_desc: Guest rode ***. After the ride concluded, she exited the vehicle and appeared to lose consciousness as she was walking from the vehicle. The *** ERT and *** Fire Department were dispatched to the location. Based upon the *** paramedic assessment guest was transported, alert and conscious, via ambulance to the local hospital for further medical evaluation.

Guest's wife states that after riding down the escalator to the studio center and then riding the another attraction, her husband requested to rest due to motion sickness. A park employee then approached the guest while he was resting on a park bench as he was showing signs of illness (nausea & vomiting). The EMT was dispatched to assess the guest and requested the Fire Department. Based upon the Fire Department's assessment, the guest was then transported tot he local hospital via ambulance.

Guest rode attraction in vehicle 111, row 1, seat 1 (left side). Guest exited the ride vehicle of his own accord at which time he advised the ride attendant  that he felt neck and back pain. When asked, the guest stated that he would like to go to the hospital. The *** Fire Department was requested to transport the guest to the local hospital for further assessment. The ride was operating under normal operating conditions at the time of incident. Guest's status is currently pending discharge per the ER.
Guest complained of pain in her lower abdomen while walking in the theme park near the *** retail store.
Guest self ambulated to park first aid station approximately 2 hours after riding attraction alleging pain to lower back and neck. Felt during initial flight.

Guest and family rode on vehicle #205. Guest's wife said he experienced claustrophobia and wanted to get off but was unsure of how to indicate this to the operators. According to guest's wife, he has a history of high blood pressure and is currently on medication for this condition.

Guest stated he had a history of back surgery 3/02. While walking through park, guest complained of back pain and transported at his request to the hospital. Guest had difficulty exiting the boat and complained of lower back pain. Guest was escorted tot he first aid station and was evaluated by a *** nurse. Guest was then sent via courtesy van for additional evaluation to the local hospital.

Guest alleges that as he was going down the drop with his hands in the air he opted to bring his hands down and hold on to the lap bar during deceleration. At that point guest alleges that the lab par pushed back on his left wrist causing injury.

guest was stepping into boat at *** load when she slipped and hit her baby toe on her left foot on the back of the seat in front of her.

Guest rode *** attraction at approximately 3:30PM and exited without apparent injury. At approximately 4:10 PM guest and family visited first aid station with a complaint of neck and upper back pain. Guest was offered an ambulance transport to hospital, but opted to go via taxi.
Guest slipped while exiting, striking her shin on the boat edge. Boat 2, row 4, seat 1.

Vehicle 8, row 1, seat 2. Guest with mental impairment rode with guardian and exited vehicle unassisted. She later began experiencing chest pains and contacted 911 directly. She was transported to the hospital for further evaluation.

Guest had difficulty exiting ride and was experiencing difficulty breathing. Assessment indicated elevated blood pressure and difficulty breathing, and guest was transported to hospital for further evaluation - released later that evening.
Guest's daughter stated after riding attraction, her father felt chest pains. Vehicle 9, row 1, seat 1.

Guest appeared to be going in and out of consciousness at unload platform. Guest sent to hospital via ambulance for further medical evaluation. She was released and returned to the park at approximately 5:30 PM.

Vehicle 8, row 4, seat 2. Guest requested to exit ride prior to launch due to back pain. Evaluated by *** nurse and transported to hospital via courtesy van for further evaluation.

Vehicle 9, row 2, seat 1. Guest reported feeling dizzy while in pre-show. Transported to hospital for further evaluation as a precautionary measure.

Vehicle 6, row 1, seat 3. Guest walked to first aid approx 30 minutes after ride completion. Complaint of headache, nausea and dizziness. Transported to hospital via courtesy van and released with no treatment given.

Guest stated he rode all the attractions at the facility but felt back pain after his last ride on the ***.

Guest entered Flow Rider, she fell off her board and her left foot hit the wall.

Guest went down slide with a previous injury from landing on side/back. He stated he had  chest/abdominal discomfort. Suggested to see a doctor if condition worsened.
Guest was riding on Flow Rider, got up on two knees. While on his knees he lost balance and fell to his left side.

Patron was standing on the deck by the river and jumped into the river. He somehow got his left big toe "caught on something"
Riding properly after coming off slide, landed feet (toes) on pad, body kept moving forward. Follow up reveals that she saw a doctor and was diagnosed with a broken ankle.
Guest went down *** slide and landed on the pad, possible hyper-extension of her right knee.

Rider hand on pad & tried to stand up, causing ankles to hyperextend forward.

Gust went down slide, landed on pad and toes went in and bent under foot as body kept moving forward. We were advised that she broke her toe.

Boy standing with his mother going down stairway fell on stairway.

3/4" cut on arm. Mechanism unknown.

acc_desc: When guest came out of the bottom of the slide, she said that she hit her head on a pole. The guest left the pool at the bottom of slide. She said that she went to a trash can and threw up. The guest informed her teacher. The teacher brought her in to first aid where the park was first notified of the incident. The guest was treated and showed no signs of head injury other than continued vomiting. Fire/Paramedics were notified and she was taken to the hospital.
Guest rolled over in the slide and injured her mouth.
Guest stated that she entered the run out and her foot bumped a pole in the splash pool.
17-yo female was ejected from the ride mid-cyle.  She fell 20 feet, hitting a fence and then the ground.
injury_desc: Multiple broken ribs and bruised lung

acc_desc: Grandfather and 5-yo grandson were riding in Big Foot vehicle when a wheel derailed, causing the car to stop abruptly.
injury_desc: Sprained knee, torn ligament in shoulder, sprained hip, swollen neck.

acc_desc: The foot tub of one of the gondolas struck a portion of the structure while 3 patrons were riding in the car.  The collision of the tub and structure shattered the fiberglass foot tub of the gondola.  One of the riders was cut under her eye by the flying debris.
Patrons both tugged on the bar as they were exiting the carrier.  It came down and hit one of the riders on the side of her forehead.
injury_desc: Bump to left side of forehead.  Patron walked to first aid, then was taken by ambulance to the hospital.

acc_desc: Child had ridden surf simulator several times before she fell off the ride and her foot went down inside the machine.  She was trapped for 5-6 minutes before others were able to break the piston to release her foot.
injury_desc: When released her foot had a 45-degree angle cut, which required no sutures, and was bent.  There was no fracture, but massive swelling to tissue and bone.  She had her foot put into a case for three weeks, and then a brace.  One month later, she still was not able to walk on it.

acc_desc: Car became disconnected and four children fell off.  Rear tub derailed from the track causing its wheels to cross brace which made the coaster stop.
injury_desc: Children had minor cuts and bruises.

acc_desc: Child's left hand caught between fiberglass wheel well and the tire.
Child's left hand caught between fiberglass wheel well and the tire.
Door to simulator closed on patron's hand.
Cut foot on broken light fixture.
Fell through pool grate.
Patron hit his head on slide #3 as he entered a turn.
Patron stated her head snapped back during the ride causing her to hit her head on the back of the seat that she was riding in.
While boarding the ride, a small child pushed another small child into a whale-shaped tub on the attraction.
injury_desc: Laceration above left eye requiring sutures.

acc_desc: Patron hit head at the end of the ride.
Patron fell while exiting a cabin.
Patron slipped or tripped while exiting the ride.
Patron broke her thumb when she collided with a friend.  The collision occurred inside the slide after the friend stopped himself during the course of his slide.
Patron lost his mat, stood up and fell, hitting his face on the slide.
State reported that an accident occurred on this date, but did not give details.
State reported that an accident occurred on this date, but did not give details.
Back pains upon exiting
Guest stuck in tube, collision.
Patron was hit in the back by another guest coming down the slide.  There were no operators present.
Patron's tube flipped over.

Child was knocked off a ladder, located on the side of the pool, by a wave.  The injured fell into the water.  The waves in the water were more than the child could handle.  During the time she was in the water, the boy had swallowed some water and started to sink to the bottom.  The lifeguard saw the child struggling, went into the water after him, and pulled him from the water.
injury_desc: The lifeguard attempted to give him air, but no air would enter.  The lifeguard then gave the injured two chest compressions, after which the child coughed up the water and began breathing on his own.  The child was transported to the hospital on a precautionary basis.

acc_desc: Patron's leg was caught in the air gate as she backed up to get into line while the gates were closing.  The girl had entered the ride area, but the ride was full.  She started to back up into the queue as the gates were closing.  She squeezed her body through, but her leg stuck in the gate.  Her knee was stuck for approximately 10-15 seconds before the gates opened.
injury_desc: Knee injury.  On crutches for 1 week.

acc_desc: Patron lost her mat and bumped her face into the side of the slide.
Child pushed the gate the wrong way when exiting the attraction and hit his on the gate.
injury_desc: Laceration above right eyebrow, required three stitches.

acc_desc: During the annual records audit in December, 2002, the state inspector noticed an accident report that should have been reported to the division five months prior.  A child sustained injuries in the ride perimeter as a result of the method in which the patrons entered the ride area through the entrance gate of the queue line.
Patron kneed in the back of the head by the operator.
Patron received a 3/4-inch laceration to his arm from the inside of the log boat #6.
Patron hit his face on the side of the slide, knocking out one tooth and chipping another.
injury_desc: Knocked out one tooth, chipped another.

acc_desc: Patron reached out to touch the ride effects and fell out of the car.  The car he was riding in ran over his right leg and ankle.
injury_desc: Pain and swelling of the right leg and ankle.

acc_desc: Patron pushed by operator and fell to the bottom of the ride.
Patron fell off tube at bottom of ride.
Patron pushed by operator and fell to bottom of ride.
Child was riding with his father.  The boy's finger was caught and piched under the stop for the lap bar when the operator opened the door.
injury_desc: Injury to end of left ring finger.

acc_desc: Patron stated she hit her head against the headrest, causing injury.
Patron stated she hit her left knee on a metal bar inside the car which resulted in a knee sprain/contusion.
Patron was in the clam shell and turned her ankle.  Accident was not reported per state law.
A young boy was sliding down the tube when he turned around on the slide and hit his tooth.
Patron closed the entrance gate, pinching her fingers in the hinge area.
Tube stopped in flume - horseplay.
Injured stepped into an open skimmer basket while in line.
Tube stopped in flume and collision occurred.
Patron struck foot against splash catch basin.
Standing in runout trough and another patron collided from behind.
Tube stopped in flume - collision.
A ride attendant attempted to put a child onto the carousel when it was already running.  They both fell off the carousel to the ground.
Patron came out of the slide at the end of the ride and landed on the cement.
Patron hit her nose on the side of the slide.
Patron had a pierced ring pulled on the right side of her chest, tearing both sides of the pierced area.  This occurred when an operator pushed down on her safety harness forcing it to close.
While riding, the patron slid down his seat and hurt his back.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Transported to hospital by ambulance.

acc_desc: Adult patron tripped and fell out of airplane, put left arm out to catch herself.

Guest was exiting the boat, which had not yet been tied off.  The boat moved and the guest fell back onto his lower back.  The guest stated that the attendant was assisting another boat and had not yet arrived at his boat to tie it off.
Patron tripped, injuring elbow.
Child fell and chipped upper front tooth.  Child said it happened while riding; mother said it happened while unloading.
Exiting boat, patron caught the heal of her foot, causing her to lose her balance and trip forward.  She hit her toe on the dock.
injury_desc: Unknown.  Patron treated at her physician's office.

acc_desc: Bumped from behind by another patron.
Two trains collided.
injury_desc: Back began hurting after the accident and he visiting his doctor.  He expects to visit the doctor again because the pain has not abated.

acc_desc: Guest claims she was stepping out of blue plane #6 after ride was completed.  Foot slipped and guest fell on right arm and right side.
injury_desc: Treated by orthopedic surgeon in home town after returning from trip.

acc_desc: Ride ended and guest stepped off the ride platform and fell.  Her right elbow hit the ground, followed by her right knee.

This child was one of three children in a family group.  During the ride, she was seated in the spinning bird's nest.  After the carousel had ceased motion, the child says she was dizzy and she fell when she stepped off the carousel platform.
Park recieved a letter of representation from the injured party's attorney stating that the guest was riding Bamboo Racer and lost control of her mat, injuring her head, neck and back.
injury_desc: Injury to head, neck, and back

acc_desc: Guest reported to the first aid office on the date of his visit that he bumped his head on the slide and cut his forehead.  The guest then left the park.  One month later, the park was notified by the victim's attorney that he received medical treatment for the injury.
injury_desc: Laceration to forehead.  Closed with Dermabond by physician.

acc_desc: Guest complained of back pain after riding as a result of not maintaining proper rider position as instructed.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Treated at hospital.  Park claims patron had pre-existing condition.

acc_desc: Guest's father stated that he was coming down slide and when he got up, his neck hurt.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Transported to the hospital as a precaution.

acc_desc: While riding, patron felt a pop in her hip and experienced pain.
injury_desc: Hip pain.  Transported to the hospital as a precaution.

acc_desc: Guest complained of chest pain prior and after riding.  Park claims history of chest pain.
Guest stated her neck hurt after riding.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Treated by private physician

acc_desc: Guest stated she slipped and fell on the exit turntable.
injury_desc: Fractured elbow.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated her left shoulder hit the restraint during ride.
injury_desc: Shoulder injury. Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest complained of chest pain prior to and after riding.  Park claims history of chest pain.
injury_desc: Chest pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she was exiting the ride platform and tripped over hte inside edge of the the exit gate.
Guest stated not feeling well prior to ride and had chest pains after ride.
Guest stated he injured his left rib while boarding ride vehicle.
Guest stated his pre-existing back pain was exacerbated after riding.
Guest stated she injured her hip and back at the load gate.
Guest stated she had a seizure while riding. History of seizures.
Guest stated he experienced neck pain and dizziness.  History of cardiac condition.
injury_desc: Neck pain, dizziness.  Treated at local hospital and released.

acc_desc: Guest's father stated that he injured his forehead as he leaned forward reaching for the seat in front.  Train was stopped.
injury_desc: Injury to forehead.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated as she stepped off train, she experienced back pain.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated as she stepped off train, she misstepped and fell, causing left wrist pain.
injury_desc: Wrist injury.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest stated she felt faint and nauseated while riding.
injury_desc: Dizziness, nausea.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she fainted prior to loading.  She is 23 weeks pregnant.
Guest stated she injured her neck while on the ride.
injury_desc: Neck injury.  Treated by private physician.

acc_desc: Guest states she had increase of twitching after riding attraction.  Guest also has extensive pre-existing medical history.
injury_desc: Exacerbation of twitching.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she twisted left ankle while stepping up to disembark her boat at the unload dock.
injury_desc: Ankle injury.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest's father stated she fell at load, hitting her forehead.
injury_desc: Injury to forehead.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she injured her right wrist after falling off attraction horse.
injury_desc: Injury to wrist.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Per guest's mother, he experienced seizure-like symptoms after riding.  Guest has prior medical history.
injury_desc: Seizure-like symptoms.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she felt lightheaded and experienced high blood pressure after riding.
injury_desc: Dizziness, high blood pressure.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated when she sat down in the vehicle, prior to the ride starting, she experienced a spontaneous nosebleed.
Guest stated that her foot got caught exiting the attraction.
injury_desc: Foot injury.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she cut her left heel when boarding her stationary bobsled.
injury_desc: Foot injury.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that she felt nauseous and had chest pains after riding the attraction.
injury_desc: Nausea, chest pains.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that firework debris hit his eye while riding attraction.
injury_desc: Eye injury.  Treated by private physician.

acc_desc: Guest stated she fractured her rib while riding.
injury_desc: Fractured rib.  Treated by private physician.

acc_desc: Guest stated a varicose vein ruptured when boarding the vehicle.
injury_desc: Ruptured varicose vein.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest complained of difficulty breathing after riding.  History of heart condition.
injury_desc: Breathing difficulty.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she slipped and fell in a puddle of water after exiting out of the attraction, injuring her lower back.
injury_desc: Lower back injury.  Treated by private physician

acc_desc: Guest stated she experienced an asthma attack after riding.  Guest has pre-existing medical condition.
injury_desc: Asthma attack.  Treated by park nurse and paramedics.

acc_desc: Guest stated she felt back pain after riding.
Guest stated she had neck and shoulder pain and numbness to her finger and both feet after riding.  Park claims guest has pre-existing medical condition.
injury_desc: Neck/shoulder pain, numbness in extremities.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she was experiencing dizziness, nausea, and vomiting after riding attraction.  Park claims guest has pre-existing condition.
injury_desc: Dizziness, nausea, vomiting.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated his neck was sore after riding.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Treated at medical clinic.

acc_desc: Guest stated that she fell while exiting ride vehicle.
Guest stated she experienced nausea, weakness, dizziness, and was disoriented after riding.  Park claims guest has pre-existing medical condition.
injury_desc: Dizziness, nausea, disorientation.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she was in the front seat and hit her head on the front of the log.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she felt dizzy after riding.
Guest stated she injured her wrist as she braced herself on the seat back when the log moved forward.
injury_desc: Wrist injury.  Treated by personal physician with pain meds and orthopedic wrist splint.

acc_desc: Guest stated she twisted her right knee when disembarking from the ride vehicle at unload.
injury_desc: Knee injury.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated he felt back pain as he stood up from riding. History of back problems.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest's friend stated she was lethargic while riding.  Guest is pregnant and was taking Vicodin, Soma, and Tylenol #3 for prior back pain.
Guest stated he felt dizzy and nauseous before and after riding.
injury_desc: Dizziness, nausea.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Two patrons sustained injuries on this date, but park failed to report injuries until 20 months later (April 14, 2008).
Patron came out of seat and landed on tailbone.
Patron slipped on wet surface and fell on right knee.
Patron abraded knee.
Child turned and hit tooth on seat.
Guest injured right hand while riding.
injury_desc: Injured hand.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest tripped while exiting ride.
Patron complained of low back pain.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron hit left side on car.
Patron states neck pain after riding.
Patron hit teeth on restraint.
Child closed his finger in the door.
Left knee pain when exiting log.
injury_desc: Pain in left knee.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron complained of neck pain.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Fell off the carousel platform onto the cement while attempting to exit ride.  She hit her right knee and wrist along with the right side of her face.
injury_desc: Abrasions to right wrist and right knee, swelling to right side of her cheek bone/face.  Patron was treated by park first aid staff, but refused ambulance transport.  Park staff advised patron to follow up with her personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest bumped his head into his mother's tooth.
Guest was hit by a wave while sitting on the beach.
injury_desc: Father reported the child looked tired.

acc_desc: Guest had a laceration to right foot after riding.
Guest flipped on tube, hit head on bottom.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest dislocated left shoulder after hitting bottom of wavepool.  Stated history of dislocated shoulder two years ago.
injury_desc: Dislocated shoulder.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was sitting in inner tube and fell back.
injury_desc: Head and neck pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Flipped out of tube in catch pool, jamming right finger on bottom.
Guest fell while exiting ride and hit head on concrete.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Child does not remember falling, so mother would like to see physician.

acc_desc: Guest stated that while getting on the ride, she did not notice the step down to the platform until stepping forward.  She then slipped, injuring her right foot and right arm while trying to catch her fall.
injury_desc: Injury to right foot and right arm.  Treated by onsite EMT in first aid.  An hour later she told park staff she would seek offsite treatment at the local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest claims that she and her son rode the attraction twice and suffered whiplash.
Child was stepping into a boat on the platform when he tripped on the edge of the boat and hit his head on the opposite edge of the boat.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that a lifeguard slipped and fell while he was getting in their raft.
Guest stated that while going down slide, he bumped his shoulder, dislocating it.  Prior history of shoulder dislocation.
Guest had completed the ride properly, but complained of neck pain.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Guest's guardian stated that patron has Down Syndrome.  Guest was transported to local hospital to get checked out.

acc_desc: Guest stated she was riding the Flow Rider and she fell off the boogy board.  As she made contact with the riding surface, she felt pain to her left arm.
injury_desc: Injury to arm.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated he was coming off Flow Rider when he hit his head.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated he was riding Flow Rider when his foot got caught under the matting.
Guest's mother stated that her daughter fell while she was helping her get into the start area for slide #2.
injury_desc: Guest's father stated that they would be taking their daughter to get checked out.

acc_desc: Guest stated while she was riding, her mat stopped.  She slipped off and continued down without it.
injury_desc: Laceration to chin and wrist pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated they were walking up the stairs, slipped and hit the back of his head.
injury_desc: 1-inch laceration to back of head.  He left the park with friends, stating he will seek medical attention.

acc_desc: Guest claimed that the mat slowed, possibly stopped and she hit her chin on the slide.
injury_desc: Laceration to chin.  Guest stated that she will seek medical attention.

acc_desc: Guest stated that he got up on his knees during the ride, fell and chipped his tooth.
injury_desc: Chipped tooth.  Guest's mother stated that they would go to the dentist to get it checked out.

acc_desc: Guest stated that she was kneeling on the riding mat.  As she went over the first hump, she fell forward and hit her chin on the slide.
Guest stated that while she was riding, she fell over the front of her mat and bumped her chin.
Guest stated that she fell while entering slide #2 and bumped her mouth on the bar that goes over the top of the slide.
injury_desc: Injury to mouth.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest allegedly slipped on platform by slide #3.
injury_desc: Lower back pain.  Guest also stated she wanted to seek further medical treatment.  Guest stated that she had injured her back several weeks ago.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest's mother stated that she was assisting her daughter into the start area when she slipped and fell, hitting her chin.
injury_desc: Injury to chin.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest bumped his head on the left side.
Guest was pulled unconscious from the splash pool waterslide.
injury_desc: Head laceration on right side, loss of consciousness.  Spinal precautions taken to prevent movement of her head.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest has Cerebral Palsey and cannot grasp with right hand.  When going down the first drop, he grabbed hat with left hand and braced himself with his right arm.  Hurt right pinky finger.
injury_desc: Injured finger.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest didn't recall anything specific on ride.  She said there were "jerky sections".  She felt pain immediately when she stood up after the ride was over.  She did not report incident to park on day of occurence.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest was spinning and fell off to the side and hit floor.
injury_desc: Small laceration and missing baby tooth on lower bite.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron was at the top of the slide and felt sudden onset of lower back pain as he pulled himself to slide down.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest walked into the first aid office and complained of pain to her neck after riding the slide.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that she was holding onto another person's tube when someone jumped on it, causing her to let go and go underwater.  She swallowed some water and requested transport to the hospital.
injury_desc: Aspirated water.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was observed by a lifeguard going under water and not immediately coming up.  The lifeguard pulled the guest from the water uninjured.
injury_desc: Aspirated water.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was floating in the wave pool when a wave knocked her off her tube.
injury_desc: Head and shoulder pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she bumped her head on the pool wall after sliding down.  She walked out of the pool and was taken to first aid.
injury_desc: Head pain, nausea, possible concussion.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that she may have lifted her neck up while on the slide.  She complained of head and neck pain.
injury_desc: Head and neck pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest notified park by letter that he had bumped his head on the waterslide two weeks prior.  He refused treatment at the time of the injury, but visited his personal physician later that day.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest walked into first aid and stated that he was riding the slide and bumped his head on the top of the enclosed flume.
injury_desc: 1-inch laceration above his eye; required sutures.

acc_desc: Guest walked into first aid office with his wife, who stated that he slipped and fell while getting on the slide.
injury_desc: Upon examination, the guest showed signs of a concussion, and was sent to the hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was walking down the slide, slipped and fell and landed on her arm.
injury_desc: Injury to arm.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that he was trying to climb out of the lazy river at an unauthorized location and, as he tried to climb up, felt a pain in his back.  He continued through the ride and exited.
injury_desc: Pain in back.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was floating in the lazy river and was struck by another guest.
injury_desc: Pain in neck.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: While trying to get onto an inner tube, guest slipped on the bottom of the pool and hit the ledge of the pool with her head.
injury_desc: Pain in neck.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated he was getting out of the river and injured his shoulder when a guest threw a tube at his arm.
Guest stated that he hit his head while riding.  He got out of the pool and sat in a chair.  He was soon joined by his father and brother who took him to first aid.
injury_desc: Head injury. Sent to hospital for observation.

acc_desc: Guest walked into first aid and stated that he had neck pain after riding and coming out of his tube.
injury_desc: Neck injury. Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that after completing the ride, he struck his foot on the bottom of the pool.
injury_desc: Pain to ankle. Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest walked into first aid and stated that she came out of her tube in the catch pool.  She refused treatment and returned to the park.  Two hours later she returned to first aid and requested to be sent to the hospital, complaining of pain to the side of her head.
injury_desc: Head injury. Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest walked into first aid complaining of upper back pain after riding three times in a row.
injury_desc: Back injury. Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest walked into first aid complaining of lower back pain after riding.
injury_desc: Back injury. Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated that during the ride his head snapped back and he complained of neck pain.
injury_desc: Neck injury. Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest rode the ride without incident.  After exiting the ride, his mother reported that he was having a panic attack and demanded to be sent to the hospital.

The park received a letter from the guest's lawyer stating that the guest received medical treatment for injuries incurred on this ride.  Letter was received 4 months after visit.  Park has no record of guest visting first aid or reporting the injury when it occurred.
Guest stated that while riding Tornado, she fell on her tailbone, causing pain.
Guest stated that when she entered the water in the splash pool, she twisted her ankle on the bottom of the pool.
Guest stated that she was riding with her daughter and they came out of their tube at the end of the ride.  Mother hit head on daughter's knee.
injury_desc: Head and neck pain.  Treated at hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated while riding, her boat was bumped from behind, which is normal operation for this ride.
injury_desc: Neck and back pain.  Treated at hospital.

acc_desc: Guest rode the ride, then walked to main gate where she informed security officers that she was feeling head and chest pain.  Guest said that she had a history of cardiac and circulatory problems.
injury_desc: Head and chest pain.  Treated at hospital.

acc_desc: Guest came to first aid complaining of stomach pain.  He stated that he had recently ridden this ride.
Guest complained that her knee popped out while riding.  She stated she has a history of knee dislocation.
Park received a request to pay medical expenses for patron who claimed injuries from riding.  The guest did not report injury to park personnel at the time.
After experiencing the attraction, the guest felt weak and dizzy with nausea.  Guest had a pre-existing history of high blood pressure.
injury_desc: Guest was assessed by paramedics.  It was recommended that she go to the hospital for further evaluation.

acc_desc: The guest's family stated that she lost consciousness during the ride.  When the ride ended, her family assisted her from the ride and into the hallway.  Guest's family disclosed that she has a history of heart conditions and wears a pacemaker.
injury_desc: Guest was assessed by paramedics.  It was recommended that she go to the hospital for further evaluation.

acc_desc: While transitioning out of the boat at unload, the guest lost her footing and fell face-forward.  During the fall, she struck her right shin against the boat edge causing a laceration.
injury_desc: Guest was sent to hospital for evaluation.  The guest's wound was closed with steri-strips, released by the hospital, and returned to the park.

acc_desc: Guest reported to guest relations appoximately 2 hours after riding to report neck and back pain.
injury_desc: Paramedics sent child to local hospital for further evaluation.  Guest left the hospital without receiving any treatment.

acc_desc: Guest claimed pain to his abdomen that occurred while riding, when the vehicle entered zone 7.
injury_desc: Abdominal pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Park was notified via email of alleged ride-related incident.  Per guest:  "restraining bar came up tight to our chests and when it came to a sudden stop I felt a jab in my left chest area".  Guest visiting his personal physician upon returning home and was diagnosed with two rib fractures.
injury_desc: Two fractured ribs.  Guest did not report injury when it occurred.  Upon return home, guest saw his physician.  X-ray showed two fractured ribs.

acc_desc: After exiting the ride, the guest reported right hip pain to park personnel.  Guest disclosed a per-existing medical condition in her right hip (not specified in the report).
injury_desc: Hip pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest reported to first aid and complained of chest pain.  Guest has history of hypertension.
injury_desc: Chest pain.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Riding in a double tube.  Friend fell out, then victim fell forward, hitting his mouth near the end of the attraction.
injury_desc: Inner halves of 2 front teeth chipped off at root.

acc_desc: Guest was riding double tube.  When he landed, he landed on his left side and felt his ear drum rupture.
injury_desc: Ruptured eardrum.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Caught ring on back of entry box.  Removed ring with snips.  Patient claimed no further need of treatment at time.  Park received letter from attorney one week later.
Collided with another patron in flume.  Both guests returned to the park to play.  Mother on one child later notified park of medical visit.
Patron collided with another guest in the flume.
injury_desc: One-inch cut between toes caused by toe ring.

acc_desc: Guest was loading herself into a double inner tube and holding on to the railing at the top of the slide when she felt her shoulder dislocate.
injury_desc: Dislocated shoulder.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: 12-yo girl fractured her collarbone while riding when the passenger she was riding with leaned into her as the train entered a sharp turn.
injury_desc: Fractured collarbone.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: As the cars entered the first turn of the track, the rear support bar of the ride disconnected when a safety pin dislodged from the bar.  This caused the cars to start colliding with enough force to shatter the fiberglass.  The cars entered a second rotation, colliding with more energy than the first.
injury_desc: Contusions and deep bruising to knees, bruising and welts on the neck from the safety belts, whiplash.

acc_desc: Patron hit head on slide.
Patron hit in face by son's head.
Patron dropped sled on foot.

Patron pinched her thumb while pulling down her lap bar device.
injury_desc: Thumbnail was removed and the area debrided by ER physician.

acc_desc: While the patron was sitting in the train in the station, another train struck the back of her car.
Child was injured while closing his lap bar when his finger got stuck in the latch.
Child was injured when the lap bar came down, striking him on the back of the head.
Patron hit her head on the lap bar, rode the ride, and was later diagnosed with a concussion.

Patron's left leg made contact with the platform as the train came into the station.  She was riding inthe second to the last seat on the train.  Her leg was protruding from the train at the time of the accident.

acc_desc: State report did not describe accident, except to say that one patron was injured.

Patron tripped while getting into a unit on the ride, hitting her head on the lap bar pivot housing causing a puncture wound to the left side of her forehead.
injury_desc: Puncture wound to forehead requiring stitches.

acc_desc: Patron fell forward during the ride, striking her mouth against her son's head and breaking her two front teeth.
State report did not state what happened, only that a patron was injured.
Patron flipped out of her tube and hit her head on the slide.
Unknown (not stated in report).

Patron flipped out of her tube and tumbled down the slide, hitting her head and losing consciousness.

Patron was climbing the stairs and fell.
Patron hit his head inside the ride.
Unknown (not stated in report).
Unknown (not stated in report).

Patron suffered whiplash from riding coaster.
Patron lost consciousness while riding coaster.
Patron complained of neck pain after riding coaster.

Patron put his arm over the side of the slide and hit something with his finger, lacerating the index finger.
Patron hit the side of the pool after exiting the slide on a tube.

Patron was injured (no further information).
Patron tripped while exiting the ride and hit her head on the ground.
injury_desc: Laceration above right eye required three stitches.

acc_desc: Patron was injured when traveling down a slide and hitting his head against the side of the slide.
Patron was injured (not further information).
Patron was injured (not further information).
Patron was injured (not further information).
Patron was injured while exiting the boat when another boat ran into hers, knocking her down.

Patron was injured (no further information).
Child hit her mouth on the guest in front of her when the boat went down the chute area of the attraction.
injury_desc: Dentist stated she has a possibility of losing her right front permanent tooth.

acc_desc: Patron injured (no further information).
State safety officials received multiple notifications of injury involving the last turn of the ride, just prior to the lift into the loading station.

Patron's had her right little finger pinched severely as the boat she was riding in entered the station area.  The boat bounces from side to side as it enters the station area and the injured had her hand on the outside of the boat.  The patron's hand slipped down along the side of the boat where it was pinched.

acc_desc: Patron went down the slide with no problems until she hit the splash pool.  Upon entering the splash pool the injured received a laceration to her left heel and a bruise and swelling to her right foot.
injury_desc: Laceration to left heel, bruise and swelling to right foot.

acc_desc: When the patron's log boat entered the transition from the flume to the conveyor, the log boat jerked and he felt his back pop.
injury_desc: The injured stated that he had minor discomfort after getting off the attraction, but did not report it at that time.  The injured was later diagnosed with bulging disc in his middle and lower spine.

acc_desc: Patron was injured while traveling down a slide, hitting his head inside the tube.

Patron injured her neck when leaving the entrance area of the slide.  She stated that she felt her head snap back as the tube went over the edge of the slide. The injured was the third person in the tube and her head whipped backwards, striking the surface of attraction shortly after starting the ride.
Patron injured (no further information).
Patron injured (no further information).

Patron was riding in a double tube with a friend.  When they moved toward the bottom of the slide where it narrows, the tube flipped over.  The injured hit her shoulder on the slide sustaining a broken collarbone.  The other girl was not injured.

Patron was riding in a double tube with a child.  They hit the bumper on the right side of the slide before entering the tube and flipped over.  The injured hit her shoulder on the ride and was diagnosed with a broken clavicle.
Patron injured (no further information).

Patron stated that during the course of the ride, she fell out of the raft while traveling around a corner.  Being out of the water, she went faster down the flume, colliding head-first into the raft in front of her.
Patron injured (no further information).
Patron injured (no further information).

Patron was traveling down the slide when, almost to the end, his tube flipped over.  The injured hit his head on the side of the slide.  He also stated that there were only two lifeguards dispatching over 6 slides.
Patron tripped over a bar which caused his flip flop and toe to become wedged, causing a laceration to his left big toe.
Patron injured (no further information).
Patron was injured upon entering the splash pool after coming down the slide and falling approximately 10 feet into the pool.
Patron injured (no further information).
Patron fell off of her tube during her ride and hit her chin on the slide, cutting her chin.
Patron slid down one of the slides head first and broke one of his front teeth when he exited the slide.
Patron jumped out of her seat during normal unload and lost her balance, falling to her knees.
Patron was injured when she was getting off the ride and got her middle and index fingers on her right hand caught in between the handle and the door.
Patron was injured when she was getting off the ride and got her finger caught in the U-shaped bracket on the door locking mechanism.
Child injured her head when the raft she was riding in took a turn and she struck her head on the side of the raft.

Patron injured her right hand ring finger when she turned around to speak with a friend and put her hand outside the boat.  Her hand was pinched between the boat and the flume, causing a laceration to each side of her finger.
injury_desc: Fractured and lacerated finger, required 12 stiches to close the wound.

acc_desc: Patron was riding in the simulator when the bolt holding the shoulder harness broke, allowing the injured to move more even though he was still being restrained by a seatbelt.
After riding, patron complained she had injured her head and neck and had numbness in her arms and legs.
injury_desc: Injury to head and neck with numbness in arms and legs.

acc_desc: After riding, patron complained of headache from head motion during the course of the ride.  The guest went to the hospital and had an MRI and MRA, with interim results of pressure on the optic nerve.
injury_desc: Head injury resulting in pressure on the optic nerve.

acc_desc: Patron missed a step while ascending the stairs.
Patron missed a step while ascending the stairs and fell, dislocating his shoulder.
Patron missed a step while ascending the stairs.
Patron missed a step while ascending the stairs.
injury_desc: Bruising to right big toe, possible fracture.

acc_desc: Patron hit his head on the slide while riding.  When he got to the bottom, he lost consciousness.
injury_desc: While being c-spined and back-boarded, he went in and out of consciousness.  He was transported to hospital via ambulance.

acc_desc: Patron was traveling down the slide on a double tube with her husband.  When they turned a corner, she fell out of the tube, striking her head on the slide and causing her to lose consciousness.
Patron lost her balance while attempting to enter the boat.  She fell into the water.
injury_desc: Complained of back pain and was transported to the hospital via ambulance.

acc_desc: Patron suffered a laceration to the bottom of his chin when he entered the queue line and fell on a metal pole.

Patron was trying to exit cabin #7 when it started to move away from the platform in an upward angle.  In response, the patron moved back into the cabin.  When she saw that the ride was not going to stop moving, she grabbed the door of the cabin that she was in and closed it.  The following day, she complained to her mother of neck and back pain, and sought medical treatment.
Two children fell forward out of the sled and traveled down the slide, falling into the water.  The sled then came down the slide and hit one of the children in the back of the head.
Patron fell off her tube, hitting her head several times on the way down.
8-yo boy stuck his feet out going down the slide and received a cut to the back of his heel.
Child lacerated his chin when he slipped trying to walk up a slide on the Pirate Ship.
Patron stated that she hit her head on the slide in the tube area because no one told her she had to place her hands behind her head.
Child suffered a laceration by his right eye while riding the coaster.
Child caught her right index finger on the lap bar locking pin while preparing to ride.
Patron was riding on his mat, head first, traveling down the slide, when his foot hit the slide.
injury_desc: Laceration between his second and third toe.

acc_desc: Patron was running in the wave pool and struck his right foot on a broken grate, lacerating the side of his foot.
injury_desc: 2.5-inch laceration on side of foot.  Treated at scene and advised to seek medical attention.

acc_desc: Patron slipped on the bottom step while entering the attraction.
Patron slipped while entering the attraction.
Patron slipped while entering the attraction.
Patron caught her foot behind her while entering the attraction and was injured.
Patron slipped while going down the stairs when entering the attraction.

manufacturer: Molina & Sons Machine & Metal Works, Inc.
acc_desc: Train slid through the brakes and did not stop at the station area.  The train continued to travel up the lift, coming to a stop at the crest of the lift.  The train then rolled backward down the lift into a closed brake causing a jolt to the train and resulting in the brake pads being sheared off from the back fin located under the train.  Two adult patrons sought medical treatment for injuries.

Patron complained of pain after entering the splash pool of a speed slide.  He stated that after he rounded the last corner, his body kept swaying side to side in the slide.  He hit the water at an angle.  As he hit the water, his right foot/leg felt like something pulled/held it to the right and his left leg continued to travel straight, pulling his legs apart.
injury_desc: Patron was taken to hospital by ambulance.  Diagnosed with a 5-inch pelvic separation and rotation, several muscle pulls throughout his upper legs and lower back, pulled groin muscles, and bruised bladder.

acc_desc: Patron was attempting to enter a boat when the turntable and the boat came to a sudden stop.  The woman lost her balance and fell into the boat.
Patron was attempting to enter a boat when the turntable and the boat came to a sudden stop.  The woman lost her balance and fell into the water.
injury_desc: After being pulled out of the water, the patron complained of pain and was sent by ambulance to the hospital.

acc_desc: Patron fell from a horse and injured her left arm.  The injured has some mental and physical disabilities.  It is unclear whether the injured fell off the horse or if she fell while she was trying to get off while the ride was still in motion.
Patrons collided in the splash pool.
injury_desc: Injuries to back and shoulder.  Patron returned to the park 3 hours after the accident.

acc_desc: At the end of the ride, the patron stood up to exit the run-out.  He was struck in the legs by another raft and rider, causing him to fall and strike his head against the ride structure.
19-yo patron collided with another patron who had stopped on the slide, causing the first patron to hit the side wall with his mouth.
When stopping in the trough, patron went over the side wall of the slide and landed on the concrete.
injury_desc: Abrasions to right arm and elbow.  Re-injured pre-existing shoulder injury.

acc_desc: The patron was riding in a 3-person raft with 2 other patrons.  At the end of the ride, where the raft should decelerate and stop, the raft did not stop.  The patron in the front position of the raft struck both feet on the run-out end grate.

7-yo, 53"-tall, 46-pound female rode the ride, then complained of a severe headache and became ill.  After arriving home, her condition continued to worsen and she was taken to the hospital that evening.  She was diagnosed with bleeding in the brain.
injury_desc: Bleeding in the brain from Arteriovenous Malformation.

acc_desc: A 2.5-yo boy was riding the attraction with his sister and cousin (5-yo and 5.5-yo).  The boy was on the left side of the vehicle.  The boy fell from the moving car (#3) and had his hand run over by the car behind him.
Patron injured (no further information).
A female patron bounced from side to side inside the slide while on her descent.
injury_desc: The injured complained of neck, back, left elbow, right shoulder, and rib pain.

acc_desc: 11-yo female had just completed the ride and stood up in the valley of the slide in preparation to exit.  At that time, she was struck by another rider.  The collision caused the child to fall face down, causing laceration and swelling of upper lip.  Patron also complained of dizziness.
injury_desc: Laceration and swelling to upper lip; dizziness; neck pain; headaches.  Treated by a chiropractor.

acc_desc: Patron was seated in rear position of 2-person raft with her daughter in the front position.  The raft proceeded down the first drop cycle and up the back wall, then down the wall to the valley of the slide.  As the raft came to the bottom, the mother's head struck the surface of the slide.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Patron became dizzy and nauseated and was unable to walk off the ride by herself.  She was transported to the hospital via ambulance.

acc_desc: Patron flipped out of her tube at the first turn, hitting her head on the side of the slide.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Patron was put into a c-spine and back-boarded.  Paramedics transported her to the hospital.  She had good movement on all extremities and only complained of pain to head and neck.

acc_desc: Patron come into park's first aid station complaining of severe sharp pain in the back of her head, radiating to the top of her head, which began while riding this ride.
injury_desc: Severe head pain.  Patron was sent to hospital via ambulance and received a cat scan.  The test was inconclusive.  The injured was advised to follow up with more tests.

acc_desc: Patron was injured when her husband pulled the lap bar down, striking her on the top of her head.
Boy flipped his tube over while riding.
injury_desc: Upon examination by EMT, injured stated that his back hurt when pressure was applied on him in the area of C3.  He was c-spined, back-boarded and taken to the hospital.

acc_desc: Patron flipped out of her tube and was in the splash pool when EMTs examined her.  She was taken to first aid.
injury_desc: The EMTs smelled alcohol on her breath.  She signed an AMA form, refusing further treatment.

acc_desc: Patron was riding with a friend when their tube flipped.
The injured and her husband are both paramedics.  They came down the slide and flipped out of their tube. The injured hit her head.
injury_desc: Head injury with nausea.  Back-boarded and transported to hospital.

acc_desc: Patron hit one of the bumpers, flipped over onto the slide and injured her shoulder.
Patron hit one of the bumpers, flipped over onto the slide and fractured her clavicle.
Patron hit one of the bumpers, flipped over onto the slide, struck his head and lost consciousness.
injury_desc: Head injury, loss of consciousness, head and neck pain.

acc_desc: Patron flipped in the exit area and received a laceration to her eyebrow.

During the course of the ride, three patrons collided.  The injured girl told state officials that she was the first patron dispatched.  Her tube stopped and her friend, who was dispatched after her, struck her from behind, causing her tube to start moving again.  At the end of the ride, a young boy was in the ride's exit run-out.  The girl's tube ran into the young boy's tube and then her friend's tube struck her tube.  As this collision occurred, the girl was bounced out of her tube and struck her head and neck on a piece of wood at the slide exit.
injury_desc: Head injury, treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron was riding on a tube with his son.  When they reached the first hill, the water for the slide turned off and the tube slid backwards, causing the patron to hit his back on the slide.
Patron was riding on a tube with her husband when her tube got stuck on the slide and other riders piled up behind.
injury_desc: Bruised back or kidneys.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron suffered bruised and broken ribs from hitting side of the seat due to sudden stop of the raft on the attraction.
Patron suffered bruised and broken ribs from hitting side of the seat due to sudden stop of the raft on the attraction.

Patrons collided on slide due to inadequate water flow and operators' failure to dispatch properly.  Male patron hit female patron's back from behind with his feet, resulting in serious injuries to both patrons.
injury_desc: Male patron injured his right foot and ankle.  Female patron fractured 5 vertebrae in her back.

acc_desc: Adult patron collapsed and lost consciousness in shallow water.  Other patrons came to her assistance and called 911.  By the time paramedics arrived, her pulse and respiration had stopped.  She was admitted to intensive care and died the following day.
injury_desc: Hypoxic Encephalopathy due to AcuteFentanyl Intoxication

acc_desc: A 12-yo girl had ridden the attraction and was coming onto the attraction again.  As she stepped onto the side of the car, the car moved.  The injured lost her balance and fell against the tension bar for the center of the arm spindle.  The injured picked herself up and went to another car, where she rode the attraction.  After the ride was over, she sat in her car and cried.  When the operator questioned her, she said she was hurt.
Two patrons collided while they were on the slide, causing one patron to strike her head.
injury_desc: Head injury, neck pain.  Transported by ambulance to local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron suffered apparent heart attack while in Lazy River.  Park lifeguards and EMT responded.  CPR was started and AED shocks were given.  Paramedics took over treatment and transported the injured to a local hospital.  Eventually his heart began beating on its own.
Patron felt a crack of her neck and felt neck pain while on the ride.
injury_desc: Neck pain.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Park reported that the patron injured her neck when she struck one of the ride's bumpers.  Injured reported to state authorities that she did strike her head, but it was not at the bumpers.  It was in the valley at the base of the first drop.

Patron reported to state authorities that she and her 5-yo daughter rode the carousel, sitting in one of the spinning cups.  During the course of the ride, as they were spinning, the 5-yo fell from the cup (between the seat back rails) and struck her head on the wood deck of the carousel.
injury_desc: Head injury, treated at hospital ER.

acc_desc: Two patrons were dispatched on the slide in a tube.  While they were still within the slide area, another patron went down the slide prior to being dispatched by the slide operator.  The second slider dispatched went down without a tube.  The solo slider collided with the two riders, knocking them from their tube.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Transported by ambulance to local hospital.

acc_desc: Two patrons were dispatched on the slide in a tube.  While they were still within the slide area, an off-duty lifeguard on his work break went down the slide prior to being dispatched by the slide operator.  The solo slider collided with the two riders, knocking one of them from their tube.
injury_desc: Pain to upper right thigh.  Transported by ambulance to local hospital.

acc_desc: Two patrons were on the ride when the tube they were on failed to make it up the first hill.  When the tube came backward down the hill, one of the patrons injured her back.
injury_desc: Back injury.  Transported by ambulance to local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron's raft failed to make it up the first incline after being dispatched.  The patron injured her lower back when she slid over the outlet jets in the slide's surface while sliding back into the first dip.
injury_desc: Bruising to back.  Transported by ambulance to local hospital.

acc_desc: As the patron's raft proceeded through the ride, it collided with one of the ride bumpers.  This caused the patron to fall from the raft, strike her head, and lose consciousness.  She was rescued from the splash pool by her husband and the lifeguard, and regained consciousness shortly thereafter.
injury_desc: Head injury.  The injured declined transport the day of the injury because she could not afford to pay for medical treatment.  Two weeks later, she suffered a seizure at work and was treated at a hospital, receiving a CAT scan.  The treating physician said that she had suffered a grand mal seizure that was most likely caused by head trauma.  She had never had a seizure prior to hitting her head on the waterslide.

acc_desc: 8-yo girl went down the attraction and "felt something at the bottom of the slide hook her in the private areas internally".  She went and sat with her mom and then her brother noticed she was bleeding.  Her mother took her to the bathroom, but was unable to stop the bleeding, so the mother took the girl to Kaiser Hospital.
injury_desc: Vaginal bleeding.  Transported to the hospital.

acc_desc: After its cycle, the ride did not come back to its final position.  This condition blocks the platform and air gates from functioning.  A child started to panic and hyperventilate after the attraction had stopped moving when he couldn't get out of his seat.  He attempted to exit the seat by himself, but was held by the lap bars that rest against the patron's back.  The injured was released from his seat 15 minutes later.
injury_desc: Irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure as a result of a panic attack.

acc_desc: The tube flipped over as it entered the bowl and the patron broke her collar bone.
A father and son were riding in a 2-person tube.  Both riders flipped off the tube and the father fell on the son, injuring the son's shoulder.
injury_desc: Child injured his shoulder, possible dislocation

acc_desc: The patron was coming out of his tube when the tube flipped, causing a deep laceration to his face.
The patron's tube flipped over in the bowl area and the injured hit her head on the slide.

4-yo child was rescued from the wave pool after being found floating.  After resucitative attempts were initiated, the child was transported by ambulance to the local ER, where he was pronounced dead.
10-yo male hit the side of the slide hard and broke his two front teeth.
Patron flipped off his tube and hit his head on the side of the slide.
6-yo boy flipped over inside the slide, hitting his head and causing a concussion.
injury_desc: Patron complained of headache after the injury.  Several hours later, he vomited and became unresponsive on the way to the ER.  A CT confirmed concussion without bleeding on the brain.  He was hospitalized, given medication, and released the following day.

acc_desc: 12-yo male patron was riding.  He forgot about the dip in the attraction and hit his face against the slide tube, knocking out a tooth.
Patron was going down with his granddaughter when a handle broke on their tube.  The tube flipped upside-down, causing the patron to injury his left wrist.

Patron stated that she may have hit her head on the slide.  She walked to first aid with her husband, where she complained of serious head pain, but could not remember if she hit her head or not on the attraction.
injury_desc: Severe head pain, vomiting.  Transported to hospital.  The claims that that she had a history of hypertension, migraines, and high cholesterol.  Prior to being transported, her blood pressure was 180/120 and pulse was 95.

acc_desc: Patron was riding on a double tube with her friend.  While going around the first bend in the slide, she felt her foot get caught between the raft and the wall.  As the raft turned, she felt a pop.
injury_desc: Badly sprained ankle.  Transported via ambulance to local hospital.

acc_desc: The patron was riding with 3 other patrons when her vehicle.  Shortly after they were dispatched, their vehicle came to a stop, causing the ride's control system to shut down the ride.  Maintenance responded, corrected the problem, and restarted the ride, but the problem reoccured, stopping the ride once again.  An operator error while restarting the ride caused two cars to collide.

11-yo girl was riding in a double tube with a friend when the tube flipped over at the exit area of the bowl, causing the injured to strike her head.  She exited the pool on her own and reported her injury to the lifeguard.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Transported by ambulance to the hospital.

acc_desc: Patron was riding in a double tube with his cousin when their tube became stuck in the bowl area and then flipped over due to strong forces of water.  The patron hit his head three times on the slide in the bowl area close to the exit.
Patron was riding in a triple tube with 2 friends when they crashed into a wall.  He hit his right foot and dislocated his ankle.
Patron was riding on a single tube.  At the first turn, he jammed his leg on the top of the slide and then heard a snap.
A locomotive and two passenger cars derailed, tipping the second passenger car over.
injury_desc: 3 children and 4 adults were transported to local hospitals for various injuries including: chest and neck pain, puncture wound, dislocation, abrasions, lacerations.

acc_desc: A 10-yo female patron was riding when one of the two vertical columns broke and fell.  As the column fell, it struck and injured three young patrons who were waiting inside the perimeter fence for their turn to go on the attraction.
injury_desc: 3 children were transported to local hospitals.  All three suffered head injuries, including one 7-yo who fractured her skull.

acc_desc: As the ride restraints were opening, one of the restraint bars struck the injured patron's foot, pinching her toes.

As the ride restraints were opening, the patron's ankle was pinched between the lap bar and the ride car floor.  He felt that because of his height (6'3"), he was forced to position his feet in a place that contributed to the accidnet.
injury_desc: Ankle injury.  Treated by personal physician; given anti-inflammatory to reduce swelling.

acc_desc: 27-yo woman was going down on a triple tube.  She was in the front, another female was in the middle, and a male was in the back.  When they hit the second turn of the attraction, the tube went up the wall and they flipped over, breaking the woman's collar bone.
34-yo woman was riding when she came out of the slide and struck her lower back on the end of the catch pool.
injury_desc: Back injury.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: 17-yo femaile lifeguard was riding when she came out of the slide and struck her back on the bricks located at the end of the catch pool.
injury_desc: Back injury.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: 6-yo boy and his father were exiting a ride tub when the tub tilted and the child fell approximately 2 feet to the ground, striking his face on a structural element of the ride.  The child may have also been struck by the swinging tub (witness accounts differ).
injury_desc: Contusion to left cheek and ear.  Transported to local hospital for treatment.

acc_desc: 12-yo girl was injured when she apparently stuck her arm out and hit something on the attraction.
12-yo girl hit her hand on a wooden post while on the ride.
Skin abrasion to thighs while riding.
injury_desc: Abrasion to thighs, treated by private physician.

acc_desc: Injured back while riding.
injury_desc: Back injury, treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Child injured his foot when he kicked the door while riding.
injury_desc: Foot injury, treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest states she struck her head at she was exiting another attraction.  She then rode another ride and this ride.  After riding tea cups she stated she had right side tingling and right hand numbness along with neck and shoulder pain.
injury_desc: Numbness, tingling, neck and shoulder pain.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest states she fell while attempting to re-enter a vehicle while the attraction was in motion.
injury_desc: Back injury, treated by private physician.

acc_desc: Guest's mother states that child had seizure after riding the attraction.
Parents stated child had just exited a pink teacup and the back of right earlobe had a cut.
injury_desc: Cut on earlobe, transported to Children's Hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated he tripped on the edge of the saucer while exiting the tea cup, injuring his chin and right elbow.
injury_desc: Injury to chin and elbow.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated after riding attraction, her heart was racing.  Guest has pre-existing heart condition and did not take her medication.
injury_desc: Rapid heartbeat.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated as they entered the attraction through the exit gate, the gate closed on his wrist, fracturing it.
injury_desc: Fractured wrist.  Treated (cast) by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest stated she injured her lip on the attraction.
injury_desc: Injury to mouth, treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest states neck was injured while riding.  Park claims guest had a prior neck injury.
injury_desc: Neck injury.  Treated and released at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest's father stated that while standing near the attraction, a shoe fell from the attraction, hitting the child.
injury_desc: Unspecified injury.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: After riding, the guest complained that his right knee hurt.  He was unsure how he hurt it.
Guest states that she ruptured her eardrums while riding.
injury_desc: Ruptured eardrums.  Treated at hospital in Oregon on the way home and another hospital in Seattle.

acc_desc: Guest complained of headache after riding.
injury_desc: Headache.  Treated and released at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she started feeling faint shortly after riding.
injury_desc: Felt faint.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she felt ill after riding.  She then rode other rides.  The next morning, the patron had a severe headache.
injury_desc: Severe headache.  Guest went to local Kaiser clinic 2 days after riding.  She was admitted to the hospital six days after that.

acc_desc: Guest was exiting attraction and, while typing her shoes, tripped on the container used for storing guests' personal property.
injury_desc: Shoulder injury.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest states she incurred a headache and neck pain after riding the attraction.  Park claims guest has prior history of neck and back treatment.
