acc_desc: Guest states she injured her right ankle as she was stepping out of the ride vehicle.
injury_desc: Injury to ankle.  Treated by private physician.

acc_desc: Guest experienced low blood pressure after riding.  Guest has history of low blood pressure.
injury_desc: Low blood pressure.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Per the child's father, when the guest entered theater A and sat down in her seat, she had a seizure.  The attraction had not yet started.
injury_desc: Seizure.  Treated and released at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest reported chest pain after riding.  Guest has prior history of heart-related symptoms.
injury_desc: Chest pain.  Treated and released at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated he felt ill early this morning and worse after riding.  Guest relates history of high cholestrol and a congenital heart defect.
Guest stated he became dizzy and nauseous after riding the first time, then rode again later in the day.  The next day he fainted and vomited blood.  History of motion sickness.
injury_desc: Loss of consciousness, vomiting blood.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated he felt rib pain while reaching to place his wife's shoes in basket underneath seat.  Ride had not been dispatched.
injury_desc: Rib pain.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest stated he had a seizure while riding in theater A.  Guest also stated a history of a previous seizure.
Guest's wife stated his speech was slurred after riding. History of high blood pressure.
injury_desc: Slurred speech.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she felt dizzy and fainted after exiting the attraction.  Complained of a headache all day and took mother's prescription pain medication prior to riding. History of migraine headaches.
injury_desc: Headache, dizziness, loss of consciousness.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she felt abdominal pain after exiting the attraction.
injury_desc: Abdominal pain.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest stated she became nervous and experienced tingling in her fingers.  Guest has history of vertigo and hypertension.
injury_desc: Anxiety, tingling in fingers.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron states the ride came to a sudden stop and she struck her back against the back rest of the vehicle.
injury_desc: Back and neck pain.  Patron treated and released at local hospital later that night.

acc_desc: Two girls, nine and eleven, complained of back pain, nausea and dizziness after riding.
injury_desc: Back pain, nausea, dizziness.  Transported to local hospital for further observation.

acc_desc: Child was riding with his mother next to him.  The mother stated she was holding on to the boy's hand at times and had her arm around him at other times.  When she turned away from him to look at something, the boy jumped from the train and fell.  She jumped off the train herself to grab him.  The child's legs went under the train and the mother pulled them out.  Nobody knows for sure whether the train ran over them or not.
injury_desc: Child was transported to a local hospital for x-rays and an exam.  No broken bones or serious injures found.

acc_desc: Guest states he hit his tooth on the metal bar on the side of the vehicle as the car made a turn.

Patron states that as she exited her seat, she forgot that she was on the top and had to step down.  She continued to walk straight as if on level ground.  She misstepped and fell, spraining her right ankle.
injury_desc: Sprained ankle.  Treated and released at local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron was stepping off the train carrying a folded up stroller and didn't see the last step.  She fell onto the ground, fracturing her pelvis.
injury_desc: Fractured pelvis.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron complained of dizziness during ride.
Patron told park she suffered two seizures while riding.  History of seizures.
Patron felt dizzy and fell after departing train.
injury_desc: Dizziness, fall.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron complained of stomach and chest discomfort after riding train.
injury_desc: Stomach and chest discomfort.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest states she had a seizure while riding train.  History of seizures.
Patrons father states his son struck his ear on the car and had trouble hearing.
injury_desc: Injury to ear.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest states she injured her neck on the log ride and later hit on back of head on another ride.
injury_desc: Injury to neck and head.  Treated by personal physician.

acc_desc: Guest was seated in the vehicle with his legs to one side.  When the attraction started, he fell and received lacerations to his chin and the back of his head.
injury_desc: Lacerations to his chin and back of head.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest states she felt nausea after riding.
injury_desc: Nausea.  Paramedics responded.  Patron transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was stopped at the "Y" utility waiting to approach unload.  Car behind came around the corner and hit her.
Patron's wife slid into him on a curve during normal ride operation, pushing him into the left side of the vehicle.
injury_desc: Injury not specified.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest states she injured her neck and back on the ride.
injury_desc: Neck and back injury.  Treated by private physician.

acc_desc: Guest twisted her ankle after taking several steps from vehicle at unload.
injury_desc: Twisted ankle.  Treated at local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest felt back pain while riding in front row of cabin 2, second seat from the right.  Park states guest has history of arthritis, knee surgery, and previous back injury.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Two children felt neck pain after riding.
After the child put in the token, he ran to the horse.  Then he slipped and hit the platform.

Fatal injury to employee prior to the attraction opening to the public.  The woman was performing a routine safety inspection when she was struck during a test run. Investigators believe that she walked across the ride's track instead of using an exit gate.
After ride, guest stepped onto walkway and her leg slipped out from under her.
11-yo guest stated "toward the end of the ride, I was about to flip over and overcompensated my turn and hit my back on the slide".
injury_desc: Back injury. Child's father requested that he be taken to the hospital by ambulance.

acc_desc: Guest states she was riding down speed slide when her bathing suit rode up her thighs and into her crotch area. She went to the restroom and found she was bleeding vaginally.
injury_desc: Vaginal bleeding.  Paramedics transported her to the hospital.

acc_desc: Patron was going down speed slide when he hit his head.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Guest was complaining about back pain after another guest came into contact with him.
injury_desc: Back pain.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: As the guest was going down the speed slide, she uncrossed her legs prior to entering the catch pool.  She complained of vaginal pain after ride.
injury_desc: Vaginal pain.  Mother took child to doctor.

acc_desc: Child uncrossed legs and sat up near end of slide; came out of slide and scraped legs on cement.
injury_desc: Abrasions to legs.  Taken to hospital the following week for infection.

acc_desc: Child slipped and hit head on the kiddie pool slide.  Bleeding stopped with pressure.
injury_desc: Head injury.  Transported to local hospital.

acc_desc: Patron cut his foot while traveling down the slide.
Patron was going down the slide with her arms on the outside of the tube and received lacerations to both elbows in the second dip.
injury_desc: Lacerations to both elbows.  Advised to seek further medical attention for possible stitches.

acc_desc: Patron was riding double on a tube when it flipped over to the right, causing her to hit her head and shoulder on the slide.
injury_desc: Child's mother stated that the shoulder was not fractured, but possibly dislocated and relocated itself prior to the child seeing a doctor.

acc_desc: Patrons were riding double on a tube when it flipped over, causing both to hit their heads on the slide.
injury_desc: One patron suffered a 1-inch laceration to her chin; the other patron suffered a 1-inch laceration to his head.

Patron tried to slow the spinning of the ride down, clothing wrapped around the wheel and injured two patrons arms.
injury_desc: Two children injured: 7yo broken humerous, 9yo possible fractured arm.

acc_desc: Patron tried to slow the spinning of the ride down, clothing wrapped around the wheel and injured two patrons arms.
injury_desc: Two children injured: 7yo broken humerous, 9yo possible fractured arm.

acc_desc: Swing tipped over on its side during operation. One news report stated that the ride had been set up on muddy ground.
injury_desc: 6 children were transported to the hospital, treated and released.  8 others suffered cuts and bruises, but did not go to the hospital.

acc_desc: Patron was riding the Storm with her nephew when she slid out of her seat and sustained injuries to her back and legs.  All parties agree that the restraint bar was latched. Patron states that she was sliding around in her seat a lot prior to ejection. She weighs 250 lbs. Inspectors determined that the restraint locks properly if the patron is sitting forward in the seat, but if the person sits back, there could be a small gap between the restraint and the patron.
injury_desc: Bruises on back, hip; swollen, bruised and painful leg. Transported to ER, treated and released. Follow-on chiropractic care.

acc_desc: 16-year-old was spinning around on a swing ride when the ride began to slowly tip to one side, then dropped quickly three or four feet. The patron fell to the ground, was hit in the shoulder by a metal bar and went to the hospital for X-rays. Two other children were also reportedly injured.
Upper swivel block broke - tub hit ground. 8yo and 57yo patrons were transported to hospital. Police reported that patients were released. No other information was given.
As person was going down the slide, he bounced and landed to the side of his right foot. His foot rolled and pulled, causing immediate pain.
Riders were told to raise their feet and they didn't. Rider's husband pushed her over too far when they were getting loaded. So her leg got caught under the chair and she hurt her back calf.
Child had hand outside of car, got pinched and run over by wheel. Parent took child to hospital.
injury_desc: Pinched and cut right middle finger, hand

acc_desc: A wheel on the ride malfunctioned, causing a passenger carrier to go off its tracks and crash into a fence.
injury_desc: Bruised knee; neck, back and elbow injuries

acc_desc: Upper main sweep nut loosened up on shaft, causing sweep to lower and hit girls. Prior to operator getting there to open seats, the girls got out themselves. One rider scraped her leg on seat when she got out of the seat. Rider did not complain of any pain. EMT suggested to rider 2 to get a tetanus shot, both parties drove to hospital and returned to carnival.
Parent reports her son's kart was repeatedly hit by another kart. She stated that supervision was poor.
Parent reports her son's kart was repeatedly hit by another kart. She stated that supervision was poor.

The drive cable of the Ferris wheel came off its track and the wheel went into free spin. Initially, midway workers and police officers at the scene tried to unload the riders by controlling the wheel manually, but the load became unbalanced. When the Fire Department Technical Rescue Team arrived on the scene, they attached ropes to each side of the wheel to secure it. One side was tied to a fire engine, and the other to a semi-trailer truck. Once the wheel was secured, the team could bring each set on the ride around for passengers to get off. No passengers were injured in the incident, but two police officers received minor injuries when the wheel broke free the second time. Investigators found that the operator failed to load patrons in a way that balanced the weight across the wheel.

Rider was riding down slide, stopped, stood up to untanlge foot from slide bag, lost her balance and fell face-first, hitting slide divider. Chin required stitches to close cut and a couple of broken ribs.
Patron's attorney stated that she had a right vertegral artery tear after riding the attraction.  Reported 2 years later.
Mother stated that her daughter injured her collarbone when their trolley hit another trolley.
Patron said she fell out of her seat when the ride started, landing on her left side. She was concerned as she had a pre-existing condition to her knee. She was transported to the hospital.
Patron stated she fractured her ankle while exiting out of the attraction. She did not report the injury to the park until 10 years later.
